(128, 'Kumpulan ZAY (Prudential)', 'Prudential has a long history in Asia, having maintained a presence in the region for over eighty years.\r\n\r\nToday, we are one of Asia''s leading life insurers and one of the region''s largest asset management companies.\r\n\r\nWith our significant portfolio of businesses, multi-channel distribution capabilities, strong strategic partnerships, customer-centric products and services, and considerable brand equity, Prudential maintains an unrivalled position for continued growth in Asia.', 33, '929, 9th Floor, Block A, Damansara Intan, No.1 Jalan SS20/27, 47400 Petaling Jaya, Selangor', '03-77127658', 'zainalabidin@prupartner.com.my', '-', 'September-3-2012-11-19-am-logo_pru.png', 0, 4964),
(129, 'Mercu Borneo Creative Resource', 'Mercu Borneo Creative Resources (MBCR) telah ditubuhkan di Malaysia dan tertakluk dengan syarat-syarat dibawah akta penubuhan syarikat pada 01hb Ogos 2001. MBCR merupakan sebuah syarikat bumiputera yang berpengalaman dalam industri pembinaan, Mercu Borneo Creative Resources bersedia menghanyut serta merebut peluang yang ada untuk mencapai matlamatnya iaitu berjaya dalam sektor dan bidang yang diceburi.\r\n\r\nDengan sokongan daripada pembekal-pembekal setia dan tukang-tukang serta pekerja-pekerja mahir, MBCR yakin akan dapat mengekalkan prestasi kerja serta mutu perkhidmatan yang menjadi pemangkin kepada aktiviti serta daya saing syarikat. Adalah diyakini dengan perkembangan positif dalam industri pembinaan sekarang, MBCR berdaya untuk maju dan berkembang dengan pesat selaras dengan pembangunan negara masa kini.', 15, 'No. 8A, Laluan Rokam 15, Pekan Razaki, 31350 Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan.', '05-3133 110', '-', 'http://mercuborneo.com.my/laman-utama.php', 'September-3-2012-11-30-am-logo-(1).png', 0, 4966),
(130, 'Lhoist (Malaysia) Sdn Bhd', 'Lhoist Malaysia Sdn Bhd is a Belgian owned company with offices in Kuala Lumpur and in Ipoh. Lhoist Group with several thousand employees worldwide today, has pursued a strategy of intensive growth and is today a profitable group and the leader in the production of Lime and Dolomite for the industry.\r\n\r\nOver the course of the last century, the Lhoist Group, which began in Belgium and then expanded into France, has progressively acquired genuine international status.\r\n\r\nOur Group''s visibility has risen markedly over the last decades. Most of our Group''s international growth has occurred in Europe and America.\r\n\r\nAs industrialists, we devote all our talents and efforts to ensuring continued expansion, guided by a sustained research and investment policy, and strong technological progress.\r\n\r\nToday, our companies total more than 5,500 people, all motivated by the desire to satisfy the increasingly varied demands of our customers, who are all confident of our mutual success. Industrial globalisation means that our customers are becoming more international. It also means that they require their suppliers to be increasingly creative, efficient and dynamic.\r\n\r\nOur challenge is to remain the best in the eyes of our customers and to prolong experience that dates back over a century.', 37, 'Block B-2-12, Bangunan Perdagangan Casuarina 1, Jalan Raja Dr Nazrin Shah, Ipoh 30250 Perak Malaysia', '05-427 1184', ' info@lhoist.com', ' http://www.lhoist.com', 'September-3-2012-11-33-am-LHOIST.jpg', 0, 4967),
(131, 'Hartamanis Sdn Bhd', 'HARTAMANIS Sdn Bhd is a pioneer retailer in Malaysia airport, it specialized in digital imaging products for more than 23 years. It currently operate more than 10 outlets, including FOTOPRO, Canon Concept, Sony Centre and Olympus Concept in the Malaysia Airport and Klang Valley. Hartamanis expanded its new business to Travel agency and high fashion boutique from Spain in 2009.', 47, 'No. 18-3 Jalan PJU 5/20D Kota Damansara PJU 5, 47810 Petaling Jaya', '03-61424932', 'hmanis@hartamanis.com', '-', 'September-3-2012-11-57-am-images.jpg', 0, 4968),
(132, 'Unitata Berhad', 'The Companys principal business activity is in the cultivation and processing of palm oil, coconut and other plantation crops in a sustainable manner.\r\n\r\nIts subsidiary companies are engaged in several downstream activities such as; processing palm oil; and manufacturing; packing/distributing of end products in the form of cooking oils, edible oils, specialty fats and soap products.\r\n\r\nUnited Plantations Berhad is one of the most efficiently managed, eco-friendly and integrated plantation companies in Malaysia and is well known globally for its best agricultural practices and high quality standards.\r\n\r\nIn Malaysia UPs total Landbanks consist of approximately 40,855 hectares. The main focus is cultivation of oil palms (90%) and coconuts (10%). In Malaysia, United Plantations Berhad operates 6 Palm Oil Mills and the Unitata refinery, a subsidiary that has been cooperating for a number of years with AarhusKarlshamn AB; a leader in the global speciality fats sector.\r\n\r\nWith the acquisition of two Indonesian plantation companies in 2006 and 2009, the total planted hectarage in Indonesia at present is approximately 10,000 hectares. A new "State of the Art" 60mt per hour mill was commissioned at July 2010 on Lada Estate, Kalimantan.\r\n\r\nUnited Plantations Berhad is known for its high level of social responsibility and environmental awareness together with the Company''s leading role in the research and development of high yielding palm products.\r\n\r\nUnited Plantations Berhad possesses considerable know-how in plant breeding, agronomy, and micro-propagation through its own R&D facilities for the development of new and improved planting materials as well as improved crop husbandry practices.\r\n\r\nThis has resulted in United Plantations Berhad being recognized as one of the highest yielding, cost-competitive and innovative plantation companies in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nUnited Plantations Berhads connection with the AarhusKarlshamn group is seen as a very important business strategy in providing traceability and thereby the ability to control the raw materials from the agricultural source to the final product - contrary to many other refineries, who have to source their raw materials from the open market.', 103, ' Unitata Berhad Ladang Jendarata  36009 Teluk Intan Perak, Malaysia', ' 605-641151', 'unitata@tm.net.my ', 'http://www.unitedplantations.com', 'September-3-2012-11-46-am-UP.gif', 0, 4970),
(133, 'Heritage Hotel Ipoh', 'Heritage Hotel Ipoh is a premier business class hotel ideally located in the heart of Ipoh City with a panoramic view of the adjacent Ipoh Turf Club.', 94, 'HUMAN RESOURCES DEPARTMENT JALAN RAJA DI HILIR, 30350 IPOH, PERAK', '05-2428888', 'hr@heritage.com.my', 'http://heritage.com.my/', 'September-3-2012-11-54-am-Logo-Heritage-Hotels.png', 0, 4971),
(134, 'YTL Communications Sdn Bhd', 'YTL is currently one of the leading infrastructure development companies in Malaysia, with five core businesses in power generation, construction contracting, property development, cement manufacturing and concrete-mix as well as hotels, resorts and leisure along with an internet strategy business and most recently providing the world''s first 4G mobile Internet with voice capabilities. Since its inception in 1955, YTL has grown from strength to strength, establishing itself as one of the most progressive companies in Malaysia while continuing to expand into the international markets.\r\n\r\nAt YTL, we believe that effective human resource utilization and efficient teamwork are vital in achieving our aspirations. With the various businesses we are in, we offer a wide range of career paths for those with the ability and desire to excel.', 37, 'YTL Communications Sdn Bhd Level 8, One Oriental Place No. 1, Jalan Hang Lekiu 59100 Kuala Lumpur Malaysia', '018-799 883', 'career@ytlcomms.my', 'http://www.ytlcomms.my', 'September-3-2012-12-25-pm-Logo_YTLcommu.jpg', 0, 4973),
(135, 'Panasonic Malaysia', 'Best known by its Panasonic brand name, Group & Global Headquarters, Panasonic Corporation based in Osaka, Japan is a worldwide leader in the development and manufacture of electronic products for a wide range of consumer, business, and industrial needs.\r\n\r\nIn Malaysia, Panasonic Malaysia Sdn Bhd (PM) has a long standing presence for more than 30 years since it was first established on 29 March 1976 by the name of Matsushita Sales & Service Sdn Bhd (MASCO) with all home appliances and audio visual products under National brand. In 1992, MASCO was renamed National Panasonic Malaysia Sdn Bhd (NPM) promoting National brand for home appliances and Panasonic brand for audio visuals and in the same year NPM achieved a new milestone of breakthrough 1st billion sales. From 1 October 2003, as a global brand unification movement of Panasonic worldwide, NPM was officially called Panasonic Malaysia Sdn Bhd (PM) promoting one brand Panasonic for all products range.\r\n\r\nPanasonic Malaysia is a company engaged in the business of sales, service and marketing for the Panasonic brand of electrical and electronic consumer and business solutions. Through our wholly owned subsidiary, Panasonic Systems Engineering (PSE) we offer professional expertise in integrating system solutions from design, supply, installation, training and maintenance of professional electrical and electronic equipments and products.\r\n\r\nPM is supported by a wide dealer network of more than 140 Panashops and over 750 authorised dealerships. To maintain customer''s satisfaction, PM has a total of 8 Panasonic Service Centres and 236 dedicated Panasonic Service Networks throughout Malaysia. Today, its operation has rapidly expanded with a total of 11 branch offices nationwide employing a total workforce of more than 400 in Panasonic Malaysia and its subsidiary, and achieving a total sale of RM1.3 billion as of FY2006.', 1, 'No.3, Jalan Sesiku 15/2 Section 15 40200 Shah Alam Selangor Darul Ehsan', '03-5543 760', 'ccc@my.panasonic.com', 'http://careers.panasonic.com.my/', 'September-3-2012-12-26-pm-panasonic_logo.jpg', 0, 4974),
(136, 'Mydin', 'MYDIN business activity is in retailing and wholesaling. The products range from food line, household, soft line and hard-line items. Hard-line products include hardware, electrical, stationery, porcelain and toys. Whilst soft-line comprises of textiles and fabrics products. Food line includes confectionery, drinks and beverages, delicatessen and dairy products. In their early years of operations, MYDINs focus has always been in the non-food sector until they bought over the first supermarket in Selayang in 1997.\r\n\r\nEach branches have their own business category, based on the capacity of goods traded. The categories comprises hypermarket, emporiums, mini markets, convenient shops, franchise stores and bazaar. Currently, MYDIN operates 100 outlets nationwide inclusive of 10 hypermarkets, 18 emporiums, 3 bazaars, 54 mini markets (MyMydin), 9 convenient stores (MyMart) and 6 franchise outlets (Mydin Mart). Each of the hypermarkets are located in MYDIN Malls.\r\n\r\nAbove all, MYDIN operates its business based on Halal concepts and stresses on honesty, sincerity and good discipline in all aspects of its business.', 47, 'Mydin Mohamed Holdings Berhad,  Lot 675 & 676 Persiaran Subang Permai,  USJ 1, 47500 Subang Jaya,  Selangor Darul Ehsan. ', '03-80736000', 'recruitment.hq@mydin.com', 'http://www.mydin.com.my/', 'September-3-2012-12-33-pm-mydin-franchise.png', 0, 4976),
(137, 'Arcadis & Towell Sdn Bhd', 'ARCADIS and TOWELL will support VALE with the program for the implementation of the US$ 1.4 billion industrial complex located at Teluk Rubiah, in the city of Lumut, in western Malaysia. This is the first phase of the VALE Malaysia Manufacturing Project which comprises the development of a regional iron ore distribution center integrated into a deep water port terminal combined with a 2 km long access trestle. The facility is scheduled to become operational in three years.\r\n\r\nAt the peak of the construction phase, ARCADIS and TOWELL will have a team of around 140 people at the Teluk Rubiah project site. The team will be built with the support of ARCADIS Brazilian subsidiary ARCADIS Logos. The contract has a duration of 24 months and is comparable to the contract with VALE that has contributed to the successful implementation of the recently opened Oman Industrial Complex Project, which was also completed with the support of a team of ARCADIS professionals.\r\n\r\nARCADIS is an international company providing consultancy, design, engineering and management services in infrastructure, water, environment and buildings. We enhance mobility, sustainability and quality of life by creating balance in the built and natural environment. ARCADIS develops, designs, implements, maintains and operates projects for companies and governments. With 16,000 people and EUR 2.0 billion in revenues, the company has an extensive international network supported by strong local market positions. ARCADIS supports UN-HABITAT with knowledge and expertise to improve the quality of life in rapidly growing cities around the world', 15, 'Jalan Semarak Api, Teluk Rubiah Seri Manjung, 32040 Perak', '05-6909500', '-', '-', 'September-3-2012-12-43-pm-arcadis__towell_sdn_bhd.jpg', 0, 2791),
(138, 'Dramona Management Services', 'DRAMONA Management Services is where your search ends and your career begins. We help skilled professionals reach their work and career goals by opening doors to the right temporary, contract and permanent positions.\r\n', 72, 'Dramona Management Services Sdn Bhd (757277U) G5, 2nd Floor, Bangunan Khas, Lorong 8/1E, 46050 Petaling Jaya', '03-7954 177', 'michiu@myjaring.net ', '-', 'default_employ.png', 0, 4980),
(139, 'Perak Hydro Renewable Energy Corporation', 'Incorporated on 14th July 2010, Perak Hydro Renewable Energy Corporation Sdn Bhd (PHREC) was formed to develop, operate and maintain all small hydroelectric projects in the state of Perak.\r\n\r\nA total of 25 small hydroelectric project proposals by PHREC have recently been approved for development under the Small Renewable Energy Program under the preview of the Sustainable Energy Development Authority.\r\n\r\nIt is our goal to fully develop and operate all of our small hydroelectric plant in accordance to best industry practice in-line with the nations aspiration to reduce carbon footprint from energy harvesting activities.', 75, 'Perak Hydro Renewable Energy Corporation Sdn Bhd 11-B, 2nd Floor, Persiaran Greentown 9, Pusat Perdagangan Greentown,  30450 Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan', '05 - 253 83', 'enquiry@phrec.com.my', 'www.phrec.com.my', 'September-3-2012-1-08-pm-pth_logo.png', 0, 4982),
(140, 'IMPIANA HOTEL IPOH', 'Impiana Hotel Ipoh  a four star business class hotel located in the heart of Ipoh offers lavish facilities set against breathtaking views of rugged limestone hills. The hotel has started its renovation and refurbishment works, which involved some of the public areas and rooms. As you enter the hotel, you will feel the Impiana flavor instantly.  \r\nThe new Deluxe rooms and Executive Suites are designed to give that exclusive and modern look. For a sensational F&B experience, step into the Garden Terrace at the lobby level, which offers a culinary tour of the best in local and international cuisine.  Indulge yourself with our tempting spread of daily buffet breakfast, buffet lunch and buffet dinner and be sure to sample our signature dishes: cucur udang, roti canai, mee rebus, nga choy kay and teh tarik. The Bistro is the place to head to for tasty food and beverages in a comfortable yet subdued setting.  With a fine selection of wines from all over the world, The Bistro is an excellent choice for both lunch and dinner.\r\n', 31, '18,JALAN RAJA DR.NAZRIN SHAH,30250,IPOH,PERAK.', '05-2555555', 'vetha@impiana.com', 'www.impiana.com', 'default_employ.png', 0, 4983),
(141, 'UMC ServiceMaster Sdn. Bhd.', 'UMC ServiceMaster Sdn Bhd was founded in 1989 by United Engineers Limited group of Companies (UEL) as the regional licensee for The ServiceMaster Company, USA.\r\n\r\nIn 1997, UMC ServiceMaster Sdn Bhd commenced operations in Malaysia with the provision of support services to nine government hospitals under the Ministry of Health privatization of non-clinical services. UMC ServiceMaster Sdn Bhd provided Plant Operations and Maintenance, Clinical Equipment Maintenance, Housekeeping, Laundry and Clinical Waste Management across East and West Malaysia.\r\n\r\nSince then, UMC ServiceMaster has successfully grown to providing integrated facility management services to the commercial, manufacturing, oil & gas, telecommunication and educational sectors. \r\n\r\nIn 2005, UEL divested a 30% share of its stake in four subsidiaries of UMC ServiceMaster group to Mitsui & Co. Ltd Group (Mitsui). Together the parties have formed a 70/30 joint venture company, UE Managed Solutions Pte. Ltd. With this strategic business alliance, UMC ServiceMaster Sdn Bhd is positioned to leverage on the UEL and Mitsui corporate strengths to provide top quality and innovative solutions to customers in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nWe are an equal opportunity employer who believes in recruiting highly talented individuals to work and grow with us.\r\n\r\nWe provide opportunities for training and development, regional exposure and career advancement to fully develop the potential of our human resources.\r\n\r\nTo reward our staff, we have a comprehensive remuneration and benefits package.\r\n\r\nIn UMC ServiceMaster Sdn Bhd., we work closely with you for a more meaningful future. For further enquiries you can email to :hr@umcsvm.com.my', 37, 'UMC ServiceMaster Sdn. Bhd. (58464-M) 2nd Floor, Block A Global Business Park, No 8, Jalan 19/1 Section 19, 46300 Petaling Jaya, Selangor Darul Ehsan', '03 7968 332', 'enquiries@umcsvm.com.my', 'http://www.umcsvm.com.my', 'September-3-2012-2-28-pm-umc.jpg', 0, 4985),
(142, 'Tasek Corporation Sdn Bhd', 'Established to answer the nation''s demand for cement, Tasek Corporation Berhad was incorporated in 1962 as Tasek Cement Limited and listed on the stock exchange the following year. It commenced cement production in 1964 with an annual rated production capacity of 250,000 tonnes at its present plant in the Tasek Industrial Estate, Ipoh against the backdrop of scenic limestone hills and excellent infrastructure.  \r\n\r\nSince then, Tasek had embarked on a series of multi-million ringgit expansions in tandem with the country''s development, culminating in the latest upgrading of technologies designed to to produce up to 2.3 million tonnes of clinker per year efficiently.', 103, 'Tasek Corporation Berhad 6th Floor, Office Block Grand Millennium Kuala Lumpur 160 Jalan Bukit Bintang 55100 Kuala Lumpur', '03-2144 686', 'info@tasek.com.my', 'http://www.tasekcement.com/', 'September-3-2012-2-37-pm-logotasek.jpg', 0, 4986),
(143, 'NSL Chemical (M) Sdn Bhd', 'NSL Chemicals (M) Sdn Bhd was incorporated in 1989 and has since grown to be one of the leading and largest lime manufacturers in the region.\r\n\r\nWe operate three (3) state-of-the-art high tech MAERZ Regenerative modern lime kiln plants with a total production capacity of 210,000mt per annum together with roller mills and hydration plants for the processing of downstream products.\r\n\r\nNSL Chemicals (M) Sdn Bhd also owns and operates an integrated quarry, through its subsidiary Kuari Atrah Sdn. Bhd., for mining of limestones for its own lime production as well as sales of aggregates to the domestic market, through its subsidiary Limetreat Trading Sdn. Bhd.	  	\r\nNSL Chemicals (M) Sdn Bhd produces high quality quicklime, quicklime powder and hydrated lime for the local Malaysian market as well as for export markets catering mainly to steel manufacturing, construction, water and waste treatments, pulp and paper manufacturing, mining etc.\r\n\r\nNSL Chemicals (M) Sdn Bhd is subsidiary of NSL Chemicals Ltd, a regional leader in lime and specialized refractory products manufacturing. NSL Chemicals Ltd is a subsidiary of NSL Ltd, a leading industrial group in Asia Pacific which has been listed in the Singapore Exchange since 1964.', 74, 'Lot 38046, Mukim Sg. Raia, Batu 5, Jalan Gopeng, 31300 Kg. Kepayang, Perak', '05-3572351', 'info@nslchemicals.com.my', 'http://www.nslchemicals.com.my/', 'September-3-2012-2-44-pm-NSL_Lg-2x2.gif', 0, 4988),
(144, 'Ekowood Malaysia Sdn Bhd', 'Ekowood, a home-grown brand has made its imprint on world map of engineered hardwood flooring. Ekowood has international presence and extensive market coverage. 90% of Ekowood products are exported to over 35 countries. Ekowood has subsidiaries and offices around the world in namely USA, Spain, Luxembourg, France, Hong Kong and China. Its strong global network consists of a combined sales strength of more than 50 professionals backed by 7 warehouses in various parts of the world.\r\n\r\nThe Ekowood factory in Malaysia has a built-up of 65,000 sqm (or 700,000 sqft) and a land area of almost 3 times the build-up. The total investment in the production plant is more than USD30million and Ekowood has over 400 skilled and experienced employees. Ekowood is a world-class manufacturer that utilizes the latest Western European machineries and technology. Due to its recent expansion at the factory, Ekowood will increase its production capacity to 2.7million sqm (30 million sqft) at the end of the year.\r\n\r\nUnfazed by possible countless hurdles, Ekowood has embarked on an unconventional path of brand establishment and management to differentiate and setting itself apart from other manufacturers or traders. As a result, Ekowood was rewarded with numerous awards and accreditations such as the below;\r\n\r\nThe Brand Laureate Award 2007  2008 for Best Brand in Product Branding (Malaysia & Asia Pacific) for Hardwood Flooring\r\n\r\nThe No.1 Brand in Malaysia when Ekowood won the Brand Excellence Award \r\n\r\nThe Malaysian Government Awards for Innovation for its product, EKOLOC\r\n\r\nRecognized by the Malaysia Book of Records for having the Biggest range of solid wood flooring\r\n\r\nAwarded Superbrands status, Malaysia\r\n\r\nBest Engineered Hardwood Flooring in the United Kingdom and Ireland for 3 consecutive years; 2000, 2001 and 2002. Ekowood is the first Asian manufacturer to have been accorded with such honor\r\n\r\nOne of the first Asian manufacturers to adopt Vlinge 5G profile successfully with excellent quality\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nEkowood is not only popular amongst architects and interior designers in Malaysia but it has also stamped its mark - visible in the many prestigious projects awarded in various continents. For example:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLuxury residential projects in Germany, Spain, Portugal, Hong Kong, China, etc.\r\n\r\nPublic and commercial applications i.e art gallery and library in Japan and museums in Germany and Spain.\r\n\r\nGolf course clubhouses and bungalows in China.\r\n\r\n5-star international hotels i.e Hilton KL Sentral, Westin KL, Traders Inn KL, Marriott Putrajaya and Pilote Hotel, Italy.\r\n\r\nEstablished show galleries i.e Mercedes Showroom, Bufori Showroom and also Proton Showroom.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nEKOWOOD - THE ENGINEERED HARDWOOD FLOORING SPECIALIST\r\n\r\nEkowood crossed-grain technology makes it 70% more stable compared to conventional solid timber flooring. \r\n\r\nEkowood floors are not laminates and are made from 100% real solid wood.\r\n\r\nEkowood floors are pre-finished resulting higher precision and even application. Ekowood floors have 6 layers of lacquer cured by UV light making them more durable and highly scratch and stain resistance. \r\n\r\nEkowood is ISO 9001:2000 certified and undergo strict tests to ensure that the floors are safe and lasting. In addition, Ekowood floors surpass international standards such as ANSI, EN, BS, DIN and JAS.\r\n\r\nEkowood is also the 1st Asian Company in the wood flooring industry to be CE certified. \r\n\r\nThe Forest Stewardship Council (FSC) and Malaysian Timber Certification Council (MTCC) certify that Ekowood is harvested from well-managed forests.', 1, 'Lot 1-12, Jalan Industri 2/1, Kawasan Perindustrian Gopeng, KM15, Jalan Gopeng, 31600 Gopeng,  Perak Darul Ridzuan, Malaysia.', '05-357 2020', 'info@ekowood.com ', 'http://www.ekowood.com.my', 'September-3-2012-2-50-pm-Ekowood.JPG', 0, 4989),
(145, 'Indah Water Konsortium Sdn Bhd', 'Indah Water Konsortium Sdn Bhd, a national sewerage company, owned by Minister of Finance Incorporated, is responsible for providing sewerage services, operating and maintaining over 5,750 public sewage treatment plants and 13,000km networks of sewerage pipelines since April 1994.', 78, 'A-3A-3A, Jln Dato Seri Ahmad Said, Greentown Square, 30450 Ipoh, Perak', '05-241 2095', '-', 'www.iwk.com.my/', 'September-3-2012-3-09-pm-logo-iw.jpg', 0, 4991),
(146, 'Charern Properties Sdn Bhd', 'The Group commenced its business in 1994 with a revitalization plan for an abandoned development in Taman Seri Rapat, Ipoh.\r\nThe development which comprised of 60 units of Double Storey Terrace House, 73 units of Single Storey Terrace House and 29 units of Double Storey Shop Office, valued at a total of RM 18.2 million was completed in 1996.\r\nThe group next undertook to develop and construct a privatized wet market, Pasar Seri Rapat, consisted of 177 stalls and valued at RM 6.5 million. It was completed in 1998.', 15, '3 Hala Rapat Baru 16 Taman Seri Rapat 31350 Ipoh Perak Darul Ridzuan', '05-313 4109', '-', 'http://www.rumahperak.com/index.htm', 'default_employ.png', 0, 2797),
(147, 'POS AD Group', 'Pos Ad Group believes that every brand goes through a brand building journey from the moment a product is launched to achieving market success.\r\n\r\nAt the launch phase, brand owners are concerned about building brand and attribute awareness. Pos Ad Medias range of products will help brand owners to achieve this objective. From Floor Strips to PosBanner, all our mediums are strategically placed to engage consumers at the moment of truth  at point of purchase, communicating your brand attributes and benefits.\r\n\r\nHowever, this engagement can be further enhanced with Captivate. Consumers are generally risk-averse, requiring several product trials/sampling before becoming convinced of your brand promise. Captivate will create a one-to-one brand experience with your consumers allowing them to see, taste, touch, feel and smell your product. This unique experience will eventually convert into a sale.\r\n\r\nUpon conversion, the next phase of the brand building journey is to achieve brand loyalty. What better way to win consumers loyalty than to reward them with great and exciting premiums. Paragon Premiums specialises in designing and customizing high quality premiums that suits your brand and your targeted consumers.\r\n\r\nCompleting this entire process is our 4th company in the group, Jump Retail which specialises in field force management. By outsourcing your field operating to Jump, you can concentrate on other aspects of brand building and leave the management of retail presence to us.\r\n\r\nFinally, OfferStation, an online buying guide allows us to reach your consumers 24 hours everyday.\r\n\r\nPos Ad Group believes in partnering with you to achieve and maintain market success throughout your products life cycle by providing brand building solutions where it matters the most  at the point of purchase', 53, '509 5th Floor, Block A Phileo Damansara 2, 15 Jalan 16/11, 46350 Petaling Jaya, Selangor Darul Ehsan Malaysia', '03-7956 389', 'hr@posad.com.my', 'http://www.posad.com.my', 'September-3-2012-3-43-pm-posad1.jpg', 0, 4993),
(148, 'Credit Guarantee Corporation Malaysia Berhad', 'Our Mission\r\n" To help small and medium scale enterprises achieve their objectives through the provision of financial and other services with the highest degree of commitment, professionalism, efficiency and effectiveness, and with all human consideration with the full awareness that the mission will be achieved with the blessing of God. "\r\n\r\nObjective\r\nTo assist Small & Medium scale Enterprises particularly those without collateral or with inadequate collateral to obtain credit facilities from financial institutions by providing guarantee cover on such facilities.\r\n\r\nThe CGC formulates and manages viable credit guarantee schemes with the participation of its partners (lending institutions), which has over 2,600 branches throughout Malaysia.\r\n\r\nIn line with the Government''s effort to assist SMIs which form the base for industrial development, CGC is now classified as a Development Financial Institution.', 9, 'Level 13, Bangunan CGC, Kelana Business Centre, 97, Jalan SS 7/2 Petaling Jaya 47301', '-', '-', ' http://www.iguarantee.com.my', 'September-3-2012-3-54-pm-CGC-top.jpg', 0, 2786),
(149, 'ASIA BRANDS ', 'In Asia Brands, we believe that our people are our most important asset. We aim to create a working environment where relationships are built on trust and respect. Building personal trustworthiness, leads us to create trust on an interpersonal level and improve relationships. As trust is built, our organization can align its systems and structure better with our organization vision and we can therefore confidently empower our people within the organization to produce desired results.\r\n\r\nIt is important for individual values to match our organizational culture because a culture of shared meaning or purpose results in actions that help us to achieve a common and collective goal. Our organization will operate more productively as a whole when key values are shared among our people. \r\n\r\nOur Culture supports learning at every stage of our work life. Opportunities in learning are available in four areas of Physical, Mental, Spiritual and Social/Emotional through our Executive Learning Program (ELP), external training programs and on the job exposure. \r\n\r\n	\r\nBrief summary of corporate history.\r\nAsia Brands, previously known as Audrey (M) Sdn. Bhd.\r\n\r\n1987\r\nAudrey (M) Sdn. Bhd \r\n- established by two brothers Ng Tiong Seng and Ng Tiong Leng \r\nand Taiwanese partner, Sincerity Foundation Mfg.Co.Ltd. \r\n\r\nThe company was marketing the Audrey and Lillian Brand.\r\nBefore 1987, the Lillian Brands was marketed by Ocean Corporation Sdn Bhd (established in 1975) \r\nwith Ng Tiong Leng as the Companys Managing Director. \r\n\r\n1989\r\nAudrey (M) Sdn Bhd became\r\nAudrey International (M) Sdn Bhd\r\n\r\n1992\r\nAcquired Ocean Corporation as a wholly-owned subsidiary and later renamed as Audrey Body \r\nFashion Sdn Bhd.\r\n\r\n1995\r\nNew management team headed by Ms.Ng Siew Leng took over.\r\n\r\n1996\r\nAudrey International (M) Sdn Bhd became Audrey International (M) Berhad.\r\n\r\n1997\r\nFirst among lingerie companies to be listed on the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange - 2nd board.\r\n\r\n1998\r\nRelocation of headquarters to present building from Bukit Kemuning.\r\n\r\n2002\r\nNg Chin Huat took over as Group Managing Director.\r\n\r\n2003\r\nAquisition of Anakku, founded by Nyam family in 1973 with a passion to create and facilitate expressions \r\nof love to babies. \r\n\r\n2006\r\nAudrey International (M) Berhad became Asia Brands.\r\n\r\n2008\r\nAsia Brands Corporation Berhad was privatized.\r\n\r\n2011\r\nAsia Brands implemented Virtual Office (VO) for all staff.', 47, ' Lot 10449, Jalan Nenas, Batu 4 1/2, Kampung Jawa Klang 41000 ', '03-51618822', ' lingnah@asiabrandscorp.com', 'http://www.asiabrandscorp.com/', 'September-3-2012-4-02-pm-asia_copy1.jpg', 0, 4994),
(150, 'Choo Bee Metal Industries Berhad', 'We are a Bursa Malaysia-listed company which produces steel pipes and other steel products. Our Group Head Office in Ipoh has the following career opportunities for candidates with the right qualifications and experiences:', 37, 'Wisma Soon Teik Aun,  Jalan Bendahara, 31650 Ipoh, Perak', '05 255 8111', 'enquiries@choobee.com.my', 'http://www.choobee.com.my/', 'default_employ.png', 0, 4995),
(151, 'TANJUNG Offshore Berhad', 'TANJUNG Offshore Berhad (TOB) was incorporated in August 2005 and listed in the 2nd Board of Bursa Malaysia. It is principally an investment holding company, whilst its subsidiaries and associated company are principally involved in the provision of integrated services to the oil and gas and related industries in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nTOB''s main subsidiary, Tanjung Offshore Services Sdn Bhd (TOS) commenced operations in March 1990. TOS is involved in providing comprehensive services to the oil and gas industry and had secured some exclusive agencies for a wide range of engineering equipment and parts such as compressors, turbines, pumps and control valves in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nThe Group commenced its marine support services in May 1995 by setting a Marine Dept within TOS and the formation of another subsidiary, Tanjung Kapal Services Sdn Bhd (TKS), a ship management / owner company.\r\n\r\nIn May 1996, Tanjung Maintenance Services Sdn Bhd (TMS) was incorporated to provide other support services to the oil and gas industry such as manpower, maintenance and repair works on oil and gas platforms and onshore plants.\r\n\r\nTo further enhance the provision of other support services and manpower supply, Tanjung NewEnery Services Sdn Bhd (TNE) and Tanjung Petroconsult Sdn Bhd (TPC) was formed in December 2004 and in April 2003 respectively.\r\n\r\nTo date, the Tanjung Group has grown to become a reputable integrated oil and gas service provider within the Malaysian oil and gas industry.\r\n\r\n Our Vision\r\n\r\nTo be the preferred integrated service provider in the oil,\r\ngas and energy industries\r\n\r\nOur Mission\r\n\r\nTo support the industry by offering our customers an\r\nintegrated services through:\r\n\r\n    Providing Quality Products & Services\r\n    Optimizing Resources\r\n    New Technologies\r\n    Enhancing Technical Competency Level\r\n    Full Compliance to HSE', 41, 'TANJUNG OFFSHORE BERHAD No. 8, Jalan Puncak Setiawangsa 4, Taman Setiawangsa, 54200 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.', '03 4252 388', 'mohdnizam@tanjungoffshore.com.my', 'http://www.tanjungoffshore.com.my/portal/', 'September-3-2012-4-24-pm-309_Tanjung-Offshore.png', 0, 4997),
(152, 'Yayasan Bina Upaya Darul Ridzuan', 'Kerajaan Negeri Perak melalui Gagasan Perak Amanjaya ingin melihat masyarakatnya mendapat agihan manfaat ekonomi yang seimbang dan mampu menambah baik taraf kehidupan mereka.Yayasan Bina Upaya bakal menjadi sebuah wadah bagi proses pengupayaan semula masyarakat merentasi batasan bangsa dan latarbelakang agar harapan baru kehidupan akan dapat diwujudkan. Saya amat berterima kasih kepada semua penyumbang dan kepada pihak-pihak yang telah membantu dalam usaha murni ini dan semoga semangat ini akan terus kukuh', 40, 'Aras D-2-1,Greentown Square, Jalan Dato'' Seri Ahmad Said, 30450, Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan , Malaysia.', '05 - 255 59', '-', '	 http://www.yayasanbinaupaya.com', 'September-3-2012-4-32-pm-yayasn-bina-upaya.jpg', 0, 4999),
(153, ' Mutual Way Group', 'MUTUAL WAY LIME PRODUCTS SDN. BHD. (MWLP) (Company No. 149029-K) started in year 1985 with a paid up capital of RM225,000.00 and it operates a limestone quarry plant in Simpang Pulai, Perak Darul Ridzuan with a production capacity of 500 MT/Hr of Limestone Aggregates in year 2009. The quarry itself covers nearly 100 acres or 40 hectares in Keramat Pulai. Since 2001, the Company has expanded its operations to include a new Clean (Waterwash) Calcium Carbonate Crushing Plant to produce good quality and high whiteness (>93%) Limestone for Export Markets such as Singapore, Indonesia, China, Hong Kong, Germany, France, Australia, Japan and United Kingdom. The second Crushing Plant imported from KOBE Steel Ltd., Japan can further wash and process an additional 200MT/Hr of Limestone Aggregates. It currently markets its products in Malaysia to both the Civil Engineering sector and Plastic Filler Manufacturers throughout Malaysia and Singapore.', 37, 'Mutual Way Group Corporate Office 56, Jalan Leong Boon Swee, 30000 Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan', '05 2545 893', 'muway@streamyx.com', 'http://www.mutualway.com.my', 'September-3-2012-4-40-pm-cropped-header.jpg', 0, 5001),
(154, 'Muehlbauer Technologies Sdn Bhd', 'Founded in 1981, the Mhlbauer Group has grown to a proven one-stop-shop technology partner for the smart card, ePassport, RFID and solar backend industry. Further business fields are the areas of micro-chip die sorting, carrier tape equipment, as well as automation, marking and traceability systems.\r\n \r\nMhlbauers in-house precision parts and systems segment produces high precision components both for the manufacturing of its own products and to other manufacturers in sensitive industries such as aerospace, motorsports, medical and semiconductor industry.\r\n\r\nWith nearly 2,000 employees, technology centers in Germany, Malaysia, the U.S. and Slovakia, and a worldwide sales and service network, Mhlbauer is the worlds market leader in innovative systems and software solutions for the production and personalization of cards, passports and RFID applications.\r\n \r\nAdditional applications are die sorting, carrier tape as well as flexible solar cells production solutions. The in-house precision parts manufacturing provides a stable basis.\r\n\r\n', 37, 'Muehlbauer Technologies Sdn. Bhd. No. 3 Jalan TU 62, Taman Tasik Utama 75450 Melaka Malaysia', '0 6 2517 10', 'azmi.ibrahim@muehlbauer.com.my ', 'http://www.muehlbauer.de', 'September-3-2012-4-50-pm-muhlbmka1.gif', 0, 5000),
(155, 'Eastern Decorator Sdn Bhd', 'Eastern Decorator is one of the most known home textile makers in Southeast Asia. Founded in Ipoh, Perak of Malaysia, the company has grown from humble beginnings to a multinational corporation. From a traditional retail of textiles and curtains to the mass manufacturing, distributing and retailing; Eastern Decorators culture of innovation has made it a profitable organization for more than 40 years.', 54, 'Lot 55992, Off Batu 5 Jalan Tunku Adbul Rahman Ipoh 31200 ', '05-2922833', '-', 'http://www.easterndecorator.com/index.php', 'September-3-2012-4-57-pm-logo_eastern_decorator.jpg', 0, 5003),
(156, 'Toyo Plastic (M) Sdn Bhd', 'We are a Malaysian - Japanese Joint Venture Company.  We are a pioneer Company Manufacturing Extruded Plastic Sheets and Vacuum-Formed Products such as Refrigerator Parts, Auto Parts, and Other Industrial Products for the Domestic as well as Oversea Market.  The Company is one of the Largest Plastic Sheet and Vacuum-Forming Manufacturers in this Region.', 42, 'Lot 56 Tasek Industrial Estate 31400 Ipoh Perak', '05-547 5818', 'toyo8@topla.com.my', '-', 'September-3-2012-5-12-pm-topla.gif', 0, 5004),
(157, 'Geohan Sdn Bhd', 'GEOHAN SDN BHD is the project driven foundation and geotechnical company with the capability and strength to deliver superior quality of service to our Clients and Main Contractors. We take pride in laying the groundwork and building the foundations for our Clients to develop world-class infrastructures for people to commute and spaces for people to work, play and stay. We provide one-stop solutions in design,  implementation and completion of projects. We specialize in Foundation, Ground & Cavity Treatment, Earth Retaining System & Slope Protection & Erosion Control.', 75, 'Co. Reg No.: 414466-K 40A Jln Datuk Sulaiman Taman Tun Dr Ismail 60000 KL Malaysia', '03-7727 360', 'career@geohan.com', 'http://www.geohan.com', 'September-3-2012-5-22-pm-geohan.jpg', 0, 5005),
(158, 'Elentec Malaysia Sdn Bhd', 'Korean based company established in 1978. Headquarter in Korea, branches in Malaysia, Mexico, China, India and Vietnam. Our partner is the world famous companies such as Samsung and Sony. Malaysia branch were specialized in Wire Harness, PCB, Injection Molding and 3D Glasses.', 37, 'ELENTEC MALAYSIA SDN BHD Lot 2247 Jalan Rajawali Baru 9 Kebun Baru 42500 Telok Panglima Garang, Selangor', '013-325 415', 'puspa@elentec.com.my', '-', 'September-3-2012-5-35-pm-elenteckl.gif', 0, 5007);
