(159, 'Medipharm Industries Sdn Bhd', 'Medipharm Industries Sdn. Bhd., founded in 1996, has been bringing quality healthcare solutions to our community through its vision, confidence, enthusiasm and creativity. Today, Medipharm is an emerging and dynamic organization which has transformed to become an active player in the healthcare industry.\r\n\r\nMedipharm started with the fundamental vision of advancing the overall quality of life of all people. Our core priority and dedication in improving and enhancing the overall health and well being of customers everywhere has not changed over the years.\r\n\r\nIn our continuous quest to uphold the highest standard in healthcare delivery and as part of our corporate social responsibility, Medipharm has launched the MediScience Health Advisory Panel and MediCare, which consist of a multidisciplinary team of qualified professionals  pharmacist, clinical biochemist and nutritionists, to support our customers with the current health and research information, continuous education through public awareness and community service.\r\n\r\nThe people of Medipharm pursue the highest levels of integrity, quality, and professionalism in providing a range of consistently safe, reliable and effective health products centered on our core competencies of innovation in research and development, quality assurance, education and customer service.\r\n\r\nMedipharms products are approved and registered with the Malaysian National Pharmaceutical Control Bureau (NPCB) under the purview of the Ministry of Health, and many of which are also listed with the Australian Therapeutic Goods Administration (TGA). They undergo rigorous testing at all levels of production, in accordance with World Health Organization current Good Manufacturing Practice (WHO cGMP) regulated by the Ministry of Health. The active ingredients used in our products are of pharmaceutical grades and are selected from reputable sources, notably from Europe and the USA. Customers can be assured of the safety and effectiveness of Medipharms products because of the extensive testing and adherence to international standards.\r\n\r\nMedipharms portfolio of brands of natural health formulas offers science-based nutritional supplements that are part of a complementary approach to personal health and well being. Its range of vitamins and minerals, skincare and condition-specific formulas, which include natural herbs, is carried by a wide customer base including pharmacies, clinics and hospitals throughout the country.\r\n\r\nThis emphasizes Medipharms continuing effort and commitment to promote a good corporate governance and also as a responsible healthcare provider. Medipharms many accreditations and approvals from various healthcare regulatory bodies affirm our commitment to deliver the finest quality products that meet international standards to customers everywhere.', 93, '-', '05-5450218', 'hr@medipharm.com.my', 'http://www.medipharm.com.my', 'September-3-2012-5-43-pm-medi.gif', 0, 5008),
(160, 'Aalborg Portland Malaysia Sdn. Bhd.', 'Aalborg Portland Malaysia Sdn. Bhd. has specialised in the manufacturing of White Portland Cement for more than a quarter of a century in Malaysia. The company produces and distributes white cement internationally.\r\nAalborg Portland Malaysia Sdn. Bhd. is majority owned by Aalborg Portland A/S while the remaining equity is owned by The Industrialization Fund for Developing Countries (IFU). Apart from Malaysia''s plant, Aalborg Portland A/S also has white cement plants in Denmark, North America, Egypt and China. \r\n\r\nIn recent years, the technological development within the Aalborg Portland Group has been dramatic. Large investments in modern technology and environmental projects have led Aalborg Portland Group to become the leading exporter and producer of white cement in the world, under the trade mark AALBORG WHITE. \r\n\r\nBeing a state-of-the-art white cement plant, Aalborg Portland Malaysia Sdn. Bhd. has implemented an environmental policy. The areas covered are environmental impact, energy, safe working environment, health and safety. The implementation of Quality Management System (QMS) is making Aalborg Portland Malaysia Sdn. Bhd. fully committed to provide excellent quality products and services which consistently meets or exceeds customers'' requirement.', 37, 'Sales & Marketing office: Aalborg Portland Malaysia Sdn. Bhd. 61A, Jalan SS 21/37 Damansara Utama 47400 Petaling Jaya, Selangor DE Malaysia', '03 7729 286', '-', 'http://www.aalborgportland.com.my/', 'September-3-2012-6-01-pm-aph_logo.gif', 0, 5009),
(161, 'German Malaysian Medical Industries (GMMI) Sdn Bhd', 'German Malaysian Medical Industries (GMMI) is an organization committed to providing quality engineered medical device and healthcare solutions to OEM manufacturers around the world with its extensive network of global partners.\r\n\r\nGMMI Is managed by a team of professionals that have extensive experience in the healthcare/medical device industries, having held senior management positions with leading multinational corporations (MNCs) in the past.\r\n', 29, 'Suite 9.08, 9th Floor MWE Plaza 8, Lebuh Farquhar 10200 Penang, Malaysia', '04-261 0875', '-', 'http://www.gmmi-med.com', 'September-3-2012-6-09-pm-images-(1).jpg', 0, 5011),
(162, 'Maybank', 'Maybank is the largest banking group in Malaysia, one of the top 20 banks in Asia and among the top banks in the world. Backed by over US$100 billion in assets, it is present in major financial centers worldwide, including London, New York and Singapore.\r\n\r\nTen years ago, Maybank began to build its team in the Philippines. Maybank envisions to be the leading financial solutions provider, committed to meeting and exceeding customer expectations in the target markets it serves.\r\n\r\nJoin the team that shares this vision. Grow with us, grow with Maybank.  We are a fast-growing, full-service Commercial Bank inviting young, competent and highly motivated individuals to consider these career opportunities:', 9, '-', '(+632) 523 ', 'hanim.ms@maybank.com.my / careers@maybank.com.ph', 'http://www.maybank2u.com.my', 'September-3-2012-6-09-pm-maybank.jpg', 0, 5010),
(163, 'B2BE GSS Sdn Bhd', 'B2BE is an international organization that helps businesses be more efficient and profitable through the deployment of business-to-business e-Solutions. Since its inception in Australia, B2BE has expanded its operations across Europe and Asia, serving customers in diverse industries and market segments.\r\n\r\nOur mission is to provide compelling and innovative e-solutions to facilitate effective process improvement, driving cost savings into businesses with competitive pricing and excellent customer service.\r\n\r\nB2BE''s team of e-solution specialists are backed by a proven track record through a wide range of industries. Our consultants bring along extensive field experiences gained through successful collaborations with our customers, intermediaries and other third party providers.\r\n\r\nB2BE range of products and solutions are developed to provide flexibility and adaptability, allowing each solution to be customized to any environment or process.\r\n\r\nthe Internet between two trading partners via the B2BE Transaction Delivery Network (TDN). Since the companies inception B2BE has grown rapidly providing to a broad spectrum of clients not only the Transaction Delivery Network but complimentary products including, Business process Outsourcing, M-Commerce Applications, Web Portals and CRM to name but a few.\r\n \r\nB2BE now operates in a number of different vertical and horizontal markets in Australasia, Europe and across the Asian rim. B2BE Group of Companies has physical presence and  offices in Australia, China, Hong Kong, India, Malaysia, Netherlands, New Zealand, Singapore, Switzerland, UK, US and Vietnam. Globally the B2BE Group of Companies employs more than 130 personnel.  \r\n \r\nB2BE now handle millions of transactions or business documents monthly. Growth in the B2BE business has come not only in the realization of key product development and market diversification strategies but through the ability for B2BE and its employees to be able to provide cost effective and flexible solutions which are backed by a strong support ethic and willingness to adapt to B2BEs customers needs and requirements as our customers businesses change and grow.\r\n \r\nB2BE has also taken the approach to develop and manage their own solutions precluding the need to use third parties to provide solutions which are simply being sold. B2BEs products are wholly owned, managed and supported by B2BE which in itself is fairly unique. This allows B2BE to be highly flexible.\r\n \r\nB2BE continue to focus on new product development and enhancing existing products to meet new needs and technologies but will continue to grow globally which will help B2BE to provide worlds best practices to local markets and customers.', 104, 'Suite A809 Jalan 16/11 Phileo Damansara 1 Off Jalan Damansara Petaling Jaya 46350', '03 - 7660 8', 'catherine.cheah@b2be.com', 'http://www.b2be.com', 'September-3-2012-6-19-pm-b2b.png', 0, 5013),
