(165, 'Carsem (M) Sdn Bhd', 'Founded in 1972, Carsem is a leading provider of turnkey packaging and test services to the semiconductor industry, offering one of the largest package and test portfolios in the world. The company has three high-technology factories, all incorporating highly sophisticated, "state-of-the-art" equipment, ensuring products which meet the exacting quality standards set by the automotive, telecom, computer, and consumer electronics industries.\r\n\r\nCarsem factories maintain world-class quality standards. All factories have achieved ISO/TS 16949, ISO 9001, ISO 14001 certifications and comply with the Sony Green Partner Program. ', 37, 'Carsem (M) Sdn. Bhd. - (M Site) Jalan Lapangan Terbang , P.O. Box 204, 30720 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia', '05 3123333', '-', 'http://www.carsem.com', 'September-4-2012-9-13-am-carsem-logo.gif', 0, 2827),
(166, 'Balda Solution (M) Sdn Bhd', 'We are part of the Balda AG group with headquarter in Germany. We offer unique one stop solution to global brand-name customers who are looking into lowering product cost without sacrificing product quality and performance. Our in-house services span from product design to high volume manufacturing of electronics products with special focus on radio frequency (RF) and acoustical electronics products.\r\n\r\nOur strong emphasis on product quality and reliability has won accolades from our customers and helped them achieve demanding requirements from their end-customers. \r\n\r\nOur relentless effort to enhance knowledge and upgrade facilities enabled us to keep up with technological requirements to produce the\r\nlatest products and gadgets.\r\n\r\nBeing based in Malaysia serves well for our offerings. We can tap into the highly skilled and knowledgeable manpower, competitive labour rates, wide-base support industries, excellent infrastructure and conducive manufacturing environment backed by our pro-business Government policy\r\n\r\nWith multiple manufacturing sites in Europe, Brazil, China and India, we as part of the Balda AG group, stand to  leverage world-wide resources to support our customer''s need for global market reach.', 37, 'alan Zarib 6, Kawasan Perindustrian Zarib, 31500 Lahat, Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia', '05-3206800', 'hr@balda.com.my', 'http://www.balda.com.my', 'September-4-2012-9-18-am-LOGO.gif', 0, 5020),
(167, 'CL Auto Sdn Bhd', 'The Principal activity of the Company is involved in the manufacture and sale of precision plastic and rubber components for the automotive industry. \r\n\r\nOPERATIONS :\r\n\r\nThe Company''s office and plant is located at Bercham Light Industrial Estate in Bercham, Ipoh. The Company accupies a land area of 16,000 square feet and an estimated build up area of 15,000 square feet. The Company currently produces the injection plastic and rubber parts and also corrugated tube  solely for the automotive industry.\r\n\r\nThe Company''s operations are managed by a team of component and experienced staff. The Company emphasizes on continuous training to enhance employee''s job performance. It is the Company''s policy to endeavour for continuous product quality improvements and fulfilling customer''s requirements or specifications.\r\n\r\nIt is always the philosophy of CLAP to deliver quality products to customers. Key personnel from R&D , Engineering and production has an average of not less than 10 years working experience in automotive or automotive related field.\r\n \r\nOver the years, CLAP has in many instances producing parts that exceeded customers quality standards. Our parts and development engineering (PDE) team is constantly in contact with customers and conducting join R&D where necessary to enhance parts quality standards.\r\n \r\nThe Company obtained the ISO 9001:2000 Certification in Feb 2004.The Company is constantly keeping abreast of changes in the automotive components requirements by obtaining information on the changes in the automotive market trends from our customers and other various sources. Eventhough the TS16949 is not a mandatory requirement at the moment, the Company is taking the initiative to ensure the products produced are conformed to specified standards. This in turn will assist our customers in enhancing their products quality since our product are part of our customer''s production inputs. \r\n\r\nThe future plans of the Company are to continuously uphoold its products quality standards and be a world class Malaysia manufacturer of precision automotive components.', 8, 'No16, Persiaran Industri Bercham 9, Kawasan Perindustrian Bercham, 31400 Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan. Malaysia.', '05-548 6598', 'mail@clautosb.com', 'http://www.clautosb.com', 'September-4-2012-9-30-am-CL-Auto.jpg', 0, 5021),
(168, 'Pantai Hospital Ipoh ', 'Pantai Hospital Ipoh, a tertiary healthcare facility and part of the Pantai Hospitals Group in Malaysia, was established in 1996. Strategically located and easily accessible within a 5 minutes drive from the North-South Highway Interchange and the Ipoh City Centre, Pantai Hospital Ipoh (PHI) initially served the local communities of Ipoh, and has since grown to become one of the premier healthcare providers in Perak, and the northern region of Malaysia.\r\n\r\nFrom a humble beginning with only 76 beds, PHI now has 180 beds and over 70 consultant specialists, providing quality care and treatment aided by qualified nurses and other allied healthcare professionals. In partnership with various health insurers and corporate organizations, PHI has established itself as a preferred provider, allowing greater and easier access to its healthcare services, which extends beyond just a single hospital through the extensive network of more than 10 Pantai and Gleneagles Hospitals, all part of the Pantai Hospitals Group.\r\n\r\nThrough the use of appropriate technology and skills, Pantai Hospital Ipoh is firm in its vision to be the trusted professionals of healthcare delivery, from prevention,detection to treatment and care, when it matters most.', 91, 'No. 126, Hospital Pantai Puteri, Jln Tambun, Taman Ipoh Selatan, 31400 Ipoh, Perak', '05-5405508', '-', 'www.pantai.com.my', 'September-4-2012-9-30-am-logo-pantai.png', 0, 5022),
