(183, 'Remco City Development Sdn Bhd', ' Syarikat Remco City Sdn Bhd merupakan anak syarikat Remco Engineering & Construction Sdn Bhd yang telah ditubuhkan pada 25 Februari 1987.\r\n \r\nSyarikat ini telah berdaftar dengan PKK (Pusat Khidmat Kontraktor) yang mempunyai taraf bumiputera, berdaftar dengan CIDB (Gred G7) dan berdaftar dengan KKM (Kementerian Kewangan Malaysia).\r\n \r\nSyarikat ini telah berjaya menyiapkan projek sejumlah lebih RM 313 juta sejak ditubuhkan dan sehingga ke hari ini. Syarikat ini juga telah menyiapkan  projek Cadangan Pembinaan Perumahan Batalion 18, Pasukan Gerakan Am di Mukim Pengkalan Hulu, Perak Daril Ridzuan. Fasa 2 bagi kerja-kerja bangunan yang bernilai RM 230 juta telah disiapkan pada 31 Mei 2011.\r\n \r\nProjek semasa syarikat ialah Projek Jalan Masuk Dari Perkanpungan Orang Asli Kemar ke Kawasan Ladang, Daerah Hulu Perak, Perak Darul Ridzuan yang bernilai RM 11,488,800.\r\n', 15, ' No. 2481-A, WISMA REMCO Taman Samudera 32040 Seri Manjung Perak Darul Ridzuan', '05-6882904', 'remcomjg@yahoo.com', '-', 'default_employ.png', 0, 5038),
(184, 'Pusat Pakaian Kime Sdn Bhd', 'Pusat Pakaian Kime Sdn Bhd, which is formed by our Managing Director, Mr Low Chin Tat, has started its first fashion clothing retail outlet at Complex Yik Yik, Teluk Intan, Perak since 1988. We are now the market leader in the fashion industry with core business ithe fashion retail, wholesale and import for years.\r\n\r\nWe have 18 retail outlets setting up across Malaysia to serve the purpose of selling all kinds of fashion clothing from China, Thailand, Vietnam and Indonesia including T-shirt, jeans, pants, jackets, sports suit, underwear and childrens garments, etc. Other fashion accessories like shoes, handbags, belts, wallets can also be found in our shops.\r\n\r\nWe do offer a wide range of fashion lifestyle products and home merchandise that cater the need of low and middle income earner group consumers. We sell fashion, but also sell service, therefore we always upkeep our branchs employees to give the best service to our loyal and valued customers.\r\n\r\nPositive response from our past sales achievement has encouraged us to expand the business, opening branches strategically located in Perak, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Selangor and etc to meet the emerging demand of the domestic clothing market.\r\n\r\nCurrently, our main office (Headquarter) is located at Bandar Baru, Teluk Intan, act as a central distribution warehouse to our retail outlet. We have experienced administrative, sales & marketing team workforce for co-ordination and supports between HQ and branches. We have well-trained and product knowledgeable branch managers and sales promoter to assist the customers in the buying process.\r\n\r\nWith great confidence, the management expects to see even more growth potential in K&M despite greater competition in the fashion industry. Which is why in the year 2006, We invested in obtaining our first clothing factory, named Shun Yan in Guang Zhou, China to manufacture our own products and meet customers demand instead relying only on Chinas suppliers.\r\n\r\nNow, we do our own fashion design and manufacture of cloth to assure products we sell are of good quality and at competitive price. We create a brand of its own, K&M fashion clothing for the local market within Malaysia. We can provide production on demand, provide ready made clothes that best suit the latest trends. We do import K&M fashion products to our own retail outlets and also local wholesale suppliers and retailers.\r\n\r\nWe believe that this approach will effectively cut our costs and haul greater profit in the near future.', 104, '12A, Laman Intan (Bandar Baru) 36000 Teluk Intan Perak Darul Ridzuan Malaysia', '05-6224637 ', 'kisscris1@hotmail.com', 'http://kime.com.my', 'September-4-2012-11-35-am-pusatpakaiankime.jpg', 0, 5039),
(185, 'Cranberry (M) Sdn Bhd', 'Cranberry (M) Sdn Bhd - is a renowned manufacturer of Premium Quality Gloves in Malaysia. The company was established in the year of 1988, and is a member company of a well-diversified and growing YEE LEE Group (URL : http://www.yeelee.com.my) in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nThe business philosophy of Cranberry is to meet the customers'' needs by pursuing quality, reliability and innovation through our own continuous research and development and commitment towards Quality Excellence. Cranberry latex gloves are widely distributed in overseas. It exports more than 90% of its products to the USA and European markets. Cranberry has its own marketing office in the USA and works closely with distributors in over 30 countries.\r\n\r\nCranberry (M) Sdn Bhd is a registered gloves manufacturer with the U. S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA).\r\n\r\nWe adopt ISO 9002 (equivalent to BS 5750 & DIN 58994) in-house quality control system to ensure that our gloves are consistently of high premium quality. This is certified by the Standards and Industrial Research Institute of Malaysia (SIRIM) and the Canadian General Standards Board (CGSB).\r\n\r\nOur gloves need to go through three very stringent Quality Assurance Gates; which includes the Water-Tight Test specified in the ASTM D5151-92, before they are allowed to be exported.\r\n\r\nOur gloves are also specifically designed and produced to minimize the chances of skin irritation caused by certain primary irritants and potential sensitizing substances.\r\n\r\nOur commitment to Quality Excellence have also earned endorsements from leading international standards and Medical Bodies:\r\n\r\n    Certified by Standards and Industrial Research Institute of Malaysia (SIRIM) as ISO 9002 practitioner.\r\n    Has met the requirement of the Canadian General Standards Board Certification listing program for medical gloves.\r\n    Conform to CE Marking requirements\r\n\r\nThese certifications and endorsements are testimony of our continuous effort in producing consistently reliable and high quality gloves and have proven to be our selling points. ', 37, 'No. 3, Jln Sapir 33/7, Seksyen 33, 40400 Shah Alam, Selangor ', '03-5192 480', 'info@cranberry.com.my', 'www.cranberry.com.my', 'September-4-2012-11-42-am-banlog.gif', 0, 5040),
