(187, 'FLEMINGTON HOTEL ', 'Flemington Hotel is a premier eco-tourism destination. Located in Taiping, the hotel nestled in the valley & offer breathtaking views of the Lake Garden. Not only breathtaking surrounding; but unmatched facilities and services at the hotel are also worth mentioning. The hotel 116 well furnished rooms and suite are tailored to the need of both business and leisure guests. Overall, your stay at the hotel will be a lifetime experience.\r\nFlemington Hotel in Perak is located in Taiping (Heritage Town). Lying in the Lake Garden, Taiping is nestled on the west coasts Malaysia. It takes around 45 minutes by car from Ipoh, Perak and 45 minutes by car from Seberang Prai/Butterworth, Penang. From Kuala Lumpur, It takes around 3 hours by car to reach Taiping.', 31, 'No.1, Jalan Samanea Saman, 34000 Taiping, Perak, Malaysia', '05-820-7777', 'info@flemingtonhotel.com.my', 'www.flemingtonhotel.com.my', 'September-4-2012-11-58-am-logofle.jpg', 0, 5042),
(188, 'Ivory Pearl Sdn Bhd', 'We are a British Malaysian joint venture company specialising in the production of wooden doors and frames for the export market. We manufacture high quality doors with innovative designs and processes and we supply  our doors to the biggest  DIY dealers in UK - B&Q and builders merchant like MAGNET (with more than 500+ stores spread through out UK).\r\n \r\nWe have modern production facilities for door manufacturing, including computer controlled kilns, door production and veneering facilities and an automatic door lacquering line.\r\n \r\nWe are enviromentally certified and our company carries FSC certification for responsible enviromental wood production and in addition, we are certified by MTCC in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nHistory:\r\nWe have been in existence for about 15 years. From a simple production operation, we have grown to a sizable factory occupying 10 acres of factory land in Kanthan Industrial Estate. We are still looking to expand our operations by going into new fields in the door manufacturing business.\r\nProduct and Services:\r\nWe manufacture all types of doors & door frames including, but not limited to:\r\nExternal Doors & Frames\r\nInternal Doors & Frames\r\nCultures and Values:\r\nWe believe in hard work and employees taking an initiative in performing their daily work. We have built up our company on its reputation for quality of our doors and innovative designs and ideas. We have pride in our doors and we have pride in our employees making these doors. Employees with the right attitute towards their work will have a bright future with our organisation. We do not descrimante against any staff based on race or sex. Foreign workers are treated equally as local workers. Our most senior employees have been with the company form day one and is still with us till today.', 6, 'Lot 5, Persiaran Perindustrian Kanthan 5 Estet Perindustrian Kanthan Chemor 31200', '05-2013007 ', ' ip-doors@po.jaring.my', 'http://www.ip-doors.com', 'September-4-2012-12-02-pm-ivory.gif', 0, 5043),
(189, 'Excel State Sdn Bhd', 'Excel State Sdn Bhd, the unconventional customer-oriented property marketing company that has been specialized in residential / commercial property marketing since 2009, we are currently undergoing strategic business reform for future business expansionAs always our company mission to maintain as customer-oriented company, in order to do that, we believes getting best and talented human capital is one of the critical elements to serve our customers better.\r\n \r\nIn line with our current company reform strategy, we are searching and inviting suitable candidates to be part of our team.\r\n', 114, 'No. 39, Ground Floor, Jln Medan Perwira Satu, 34600 Kamunting, Perak ', '05-806 0097', '-', '-', 'September-4-2012-12-11-pm-excelstate.jpg', 0, 5044),
(190, 'Maju Weko Timber Industries Sdn Bhd', ' Maju Weko Timber Industries Sdn. Bhd. ["Maju Weko"] is a wholly - owned subsidiary company of Leweko Resources Berhad, a company listed on the Second Board of Bursa Malaysia Securities Berhad (formerly known as Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange), with a market capitalisation of approximately RM196 million as of 31 July 2004. Maju Weko is  principally involves in logs trading, processing the manufacture of sawn timber, moulded timber and other timber related products. The Company began its business in 1973 with sawmilling operations producing only rough sawn timber. In 1998, it diversified into timber moulding and since then, the production of moulded timber, both in volume and product range, has grown substantially. This is due to the Company''s high investment in acquiring of modern equipment, training of staff and doubling the kiln drying capacity.  \r\n\r\nMaju Weko has earned a reputation as a dependable and quality of timber based products over the years. The ability to produce quality products is assisted by the fact that the Company presently has the rights to extract logs from its own forest concessions currently we are komo certified. In addition, the Company also has agreements with other forest concession holders to purchase logs extracted from their concessions. This availability of wood resources ensure that the Company has a consistent and sustainable supply of logs to meet its long term production needs for at least the next 8 to 10 years. Maju Weko has been and will continue to be a long term player in the tropical timber industry and towards this end, it is carrying out an on-going process to apply for new concessions from the authorities and to sign up long term supply agreements with other forest concessionaires to ensure that it has a continuous supply of logs.\r\n\r\nMaju Weko has successfully established strong and long term business relationships with a number of the major buyers of timber products in the United States of America, Australia, the European Union as well as local customers in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nMaju Weko fully supports the Malaysian Government''s and international  policies on environmental preservation and sustainable forest management. As the Company''s forest concessions are within the State of Perak Darul Ridzuan, Malaysia (which has been awarded the Certificate for Forest Management by the Malaysian Timber Certification Council ["MTCS"] in 2003), its forest management and harvesting activities are in compliance with sustainable forest management practices. Since then, we are MTCS certified under FCOC OID (CHAIN OF CUSTODY) and FSC certified under COC 062 (CHAIN OF CUSTODY).', 59, ' 36-38 Lengkok Tasek Timur Taman Tasek Indra, 31400 Ipoh, ', '05-5486663', 'majuweko@tm.net.my ', 'http://www.majuweko.com.my', 'September-4-2012-12-17-pm-logomw.JPG', 0, 5046),
