(197, 'Hua Yang  Berhad', 'Hua Yang Berhad (Hua Yang) started with a man''s passion and dream, the late Mr. Ho Mok Heng, who had a vision of a developing country. We started on December 28th, 1978 with a private limited company under the name of Heng Po Sdn Bhd. Later it was changed to Hua Yang Development Sdn Bhd on March 10th, 1979. From there, Hua Yang established a solid reputation as a trustworthy, responsible and reliable developer. After years of significant growth and expansion, the name was changed to simply Hua Yang Sdn Bhd on September 4th, 2001. Very soon after, we were listed on the Main Board of Bursa Malaysia on November 29th, 2002 and took our present name on September 12th, 2001.\r\n\r\nHua Yang''s principal activities consist of investment holding, property development and provision of management services. Its subsidiary companies currently are involved in investment holding, provision of management services, property development and building construction.\r\n\r\nThe property development activities of the Hua Yang Group are currently being undertaken on their land bank which are located mainly in Klang Valley, Perak and Johor. ', 44, '123, Jalan Raja Permaisuri Bainun (Jalan Kampar), 30250 Ipoh, Perak', '05-2543 812', 'ipoh@huayang.com.my ', 'http://huayang.com.my', 'September-4-2012-12-47-pm-930.jpg', 0, 5052),
(198, 'Kumpulan Barkath', 'With numerous products being manufactured, Kumpulan Barkath is today widely referred to as "The Family food People". \r\n\r\nBrands such as Hacks, Sunquick, Kings, Mayens and ClassFoods have become household names and have positioned the company as market leader in food manufacturing.\r\n\r\nIn addition, Kumpulan Barkath is an exclusive distributor of a number of quality products manufactured both by Malaysian as well as foreign companies.\r\n\r\nThe history of Kumpulan Barkath traces back to 1945 when a visionary entrepreneur, the late Haji Abu Backer bin Mohd Hussain founded a sundry shop called BARKATH STORES at Union Street, Penang. \r\n\r\nWith good business acumen, Haji Abu Backer turned BARKATH STORES from a small family business to a profitable business venture, beginning with the local manufacture of Hacks sweets originally from the U.K. and other confectioneries including processing of frozen foods.\r\n\r\nToday, BARKATH STORES still operates as part of KUMPULAN BARKATH, a group of 22 companies based in Malaysia, Singapore, Indonesia, India and U.K. involved in manufacturing, import-export, distribution, property development, investment, and communications. \r\n\r\nKUMPULAN BAKATH has become a household name in the ASEAN region, known for its high quality confectionery, concentrated fruit juice and convenience consumer products, accentuating the Group into a leading food manufacturer, importer, exporter, distributor and contract manufacturer in the region.\r\n\r\nPRIZE-winning display. Barkath Stores,Kuala Lumpur, in the ''50s.\r\n\r\nService on 3 wheels. ''fast food'' of the ''50s. \r\n\r\nROYAL VISIT.Queen Elizabeth stopping by at the Hacks pavilion during an official visit to Penang in the ''60s.\r\nChallenges For The Future\r\nIn coming years, Kumpulan Barkath is committed to achieving the highest success - not only for itself, but for the greater good of all.\r\n\r\nThe Group will continue to uphold Quality in all its products in the spirit of Excellence and Dedication. It has achieved as one of its foremost goals the achievement of the prestigious ISO 9002 Certification awarded by SIRIM.\r\n\r\nKumpulan Barkath believes that a dedicated and experienced workforce is vital in all aspects of its trading and manufacturing operations and is fortunate to have a team of loyal staff, some of whom have been serving the Company for more than thirty years. In creating a conducive and caring enviroment for employees, it has also fostered closer ties between them and the management.\r\n\r\nKumpulan Barkath also has a strong commitment to the country''s social development and has contributed regularly towards such events as Starwalk, school events and other charitable functions. It is poised to play an important role in helping Malaysia achieve its industrial goals as envisioned in Wawasan 2020.', 104, 'Bangunan Barkath 4th Floor, 21 Beach Street,  10300 Penang, Malaysia.', '04-2626252', ' ayob@barkath.com', 'http://www.barkath.com', 'September-4-2012-12-51-pm-KUMPULAN-BARKATH.jpg', 0, 5055),
(199, 'Decagon Lab & Analytical Testing S/B', 'Decagon Lab & Analytical Testing Sdn Bhd is an analytical laboratory, employing professionals and experienced employees of more than 10 years in the ion exchange resin study/analysis, water and wastewater analysis and microbiology analysis. \r\n\r\nDecagon lab presents a wide range of testing services with precision results. Decagon lab is MS ISO/IEC 17025:2005 certified and has highly experienced laboratory personnel and technical instrumentation.\r\n\r\n', 10, '	DECAGON LAB & ANALYTICAL TESTING S/B 12-A, TKT 1, JLN SG BURUNG U32/U, BUKIT RIMAU , SEK 32, 40460 SHAH ALAM', '603-5121 61', ' info@decagonlab.com', 'http://www.decagonlab.com', 'September-4-2012-1-30-pm-decagonlab.png', 0, 5056),
