(208, 'MH Hotels Sdn. Bhd. ', 'MH Hotels Sdn. Bhd. launched MH Hotels Ipoh on 22nd Dec 2011 marking the completion of the first phase of a multimillion dollar hotel project.\r\n\r\nComplete with unique modern rooms, full amenities and services, MH Hotels Ipoh presents contemporary Club suites, Ladies themed rooms, daringly designed industrial themed rooms, a executive lounge, tastefully designed lobby and grand ballroom and hosts two exciting dining outlets: Unique Seafood Restaurant and a sky lounge (Pork Free). In addition, the hotel also facilitates a SPA, foot reflexology centre, and a executive lounge to ease away the tiredness of every weary traveled guest.\r\n\r\n\r\nMH Hotels Sdn Bhd aims to be the next generation of corporate Boutique Hotel which is vibrant, unpretentious, and flexible. We believe that todays traveler want to engage all senses whether at work or at play. MH Hotels Ipoh has a fresh and energetic vibe and inspires patrons with an unexpected touch that fuels creativity yet allow time to recharge and relax. Service is less bound by protocol but is enthusiastic and intuitive. MH Hotels Ipoh represent passionate hospitality wrapped up in a stylish package and with it is product designs, MH Hotels Ipoh perfectly embodies those criteria said David Loong, Chief Operation Officer of MH Hotels Sdn Bhd.\r\n\r\nBasic Room Overview\r\nThe hotel offers tastefully designed rooms and suites, ranging in size from 400sq feet to 1000sq feet offering a lineup of near hardware and amenities. Standard room features include LCD televisions, high speed Wi-Fi services, power charging Chubb safes, and coffee and tea making facilities.\r\n\r\nFor Guests Conveniences & Entertainment\r\nConveniently linked to lifestyle and entertainment options via a 5-10minutes walk, MH Hotels Ipoh sits strategically amongst corporate offices and companies in the heart of Ipohs business district. Apart from an excellent location, the Grand Ballroom located on the 5th Floor and Seminar rooms on the 6th Floor features up to date audiovisual equipments and built in LED TVs. The spacious modern and soundproofed 12,000sq feet ballroom can accommodate up to 580 persons and the 5,000 sq feet seminar hall named THE GALLERY can accommodate up to 200 persons.\r\n\r\nThe hotels Coffeehouse offers mouth-watering local delicacies and irresistible desserts. Another facility to uplift the feel of guests is our very own Sky lounge, a wonderful place to be entertained, unwind and chill out with a group of friends, colleagues and business associates or private moments alone just to capture the scenic moment. Step in to MH Hotels Ipoh a different personal experience  STAY MH, STAY DIFFERENT\r\n', 1, 'PT 21 2695B, Jalan Median Ipoh 1A, Medan Ipoh Bistari 31400 Ipoh, Perak', '05 545 1000', 'may@mhhotels.com.my', 'http://www.mhhotels.com.my', 'September-4-2012-3-23-pm-foot_sig.jpg', 0, 5070),
(209, 'Belati Wangsa (M) Sdn Bhd', 'Belati Wangsa (M) Sdn. Bhd. (BWSB) a subsidiary of Johawaki Sdn. Bhd., is a reputable road management company which has been entrusted with the maintenance of Federal roads in the Northern Zone of the Peninsular Malaysia.\r\nOn December 22, 2000 , the company signed a 15-year concession agreement with the Government for the management and maintenance of 2,600 km of roads, including Federal Roads (Main), Federal Roads (Felda), Road Entrance to Federal Institution and Industrial Roads, in the states of Perak, Pulau Pinang, Kedah and Perlis. It took over the management of these roads on February 16, 2001 .\r\nIn this agreement, the company is responsible for carrying out routine, periodical and emergency works along these roads. BWSB has more than 150 sub-contractors in the four states.\r\nThe company has a staff strength of about 250 comprising engineers, technical assistants, technicians, drivers and general workers.\r\nThe company headquarter in Ipoh, Perak, and has 10 area offices in Kinta, Gerik, Tapah, Sitiawan, Taiping, Alor Setar, Langkawi, Kulim, Kangar and Penang.\r\n\r\n', 15, 'No 2A, Jalan Raja Dr Nazrin Shah (Jalan Gopeng), Ipoh Perak Darul Ridzuan 30250 Malaysia', '052552211', '	bwsb@belatiwangsa.com.my', '	 http://www.belatiwangsa.com.my', 'September-4-2012-3-25-pm-belatpg.gif', 0, 5069),
