(215, 'MH Hotel Ipoh', 'MH Hotels Ipoh, a new hotel in Ipoh located conspicuously at the entry to Ipoh if travelling along the North-South Highway (or exit to Bercham and Tanjung Rambutan) at the corner lot of Jalan Medan Ipoh 1A in Medan Ipoh Bistari, opened for business at the end of December, 2011, beginning with 50 rooms initially. Facilities like club lounge, foot reflexology centre, seminar rooms and ballroom will only be ready in three months time.', 31, 'PT 21 2695B, Jalan Median Ipoh 1A, Medan Ipoh Bistari 31400 Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan, Malaysia.', '05 545 1000', 'hr.rec@mhhotels.com.my / nages@mhhotels.com.my', 'http://www.mhhotels.com.my', 'September-4-2012-4-47-pm-mh-hotel.jpg', 0, 5078),
(216, '1926 Heritage Hotel Penang', 'Built in 1926, the property once served as a home to British colonial immigration officers and local administrators of Penang. Located off Imigresen Road and Burma Road, 1926 Heritage Hotel occupies 24 heritage link houses beautifully restored to its former glory.\r\n\r\nIn 1999 The State Government of Penang under PDC (Penang Development Corporation) invested a significant amount of funds to refurbish this colonial property as a heritage hotel with most of its Anglo-Malay architectural essence still intact. Surrounded by spacious rooms, wooden interiors, long corridors, balmy balconies, beautiful victorian windows as well as pictures of the old Penang, a sense of nostalgia can be felt throughout the property. And we top that experience with warm, friendly service.\r\n\r\nThe Hotel is conveniently located in the heart of the historic city of Georgetown, founded in 1786 by Captain Francis Light. Listed as a UNESCO heritage city, Georgetown is a one of a kind melting pot of cultures, heritage, foods and festivals from diverse communities.\r\n\r\nOur Philosophy\r\n1926 Heritage Hotel is all about bringing you the wholesome experience of the British colonial era and the spirit of Malaysian hospitality from the very moment you step into our lobby. We at 1926 Heritage Hotel are ever ready to go the extra mile to ensure your stay with us will be most memorable. Your satisfaction is our number one priority and we hope that every second you spend with us will be filled with nostalgia of the colonial era.\r\n\r\n', 1, '227, Jalan Burma, 10050 Penang, Malaysia.', '04-2281926 ', 'memee@1926heritagehotel.vom.my', 'http://www.1926heritagehotel.com/', 'September-4-2012-4-56-pm-heratage.gif', 0, 5079),
(217, 'YTY Industries Sdn Bhd', 'Established in 1988, we have been producing a diversified range of high quality and innovative medical examination gloves for the world market for over 22 years.\r\n \r\nFrom a company with 6 production lines, we have grown to a group of companies having 2 ultra modern manufacturing plants with over 50 production lines, and still growing.\r\n \r\nLocated in the state of Perak in Malaysia, we employ over 1,800 dedicated and trained staff.\r\n \r\nOur gloves are found in a wide spectrum of industries including:-\r\n \r\n	Medical		Automotive\r\n	Dental		F& B Services\r\n	Laboratories		Janitorial Services\r\n	Nursing Homes		Safety\r\n	Law Enforcement	 	 \r\n \r\nOur gloves are mainly distributed in USA, United Kingdom, Germany, Italy, Norway, Japan, Singapore and Korea.', 1, 'B-3A-32, Block B, No. 1, Jalan Tropicana Selatan 1, 47410 Petaling Jaya, Selangor Darul Ehsan, Malaysia', '03 7885 018', 'inquiry@ytygroup.com.my', 'http://www.ytygroup.com.my', 'September-4-2012-5-02-pm-logo_yty.jpg', 0, 5082),
