(219, 'E-Komoditi', 'E-Komoditi Sdn. Bhd. (490254-U), an MSC Status Company was established in 1999 with the specialization in building e-business communities and providing e-business solutions globally.\r\n\r\nWe provide Tier 1 and Tier 2 ERP tools and customised systems as well as e-Commerce infrastructure and solutions such as e-procurement systems and payment gateways for medium to large organizations and government/semi government agencies.\r\n\r\nE-Komoditi also provides Software Development /Customisation, Web Hosting and Professional Services. E-Komoditi is partly owned by public listed HeiTech Padu Bhd.\r\n\r\nOur Vision\r\n\r\nE-Komoditi was established with the vision of enabling Business entities for e-business and e-commerce without the risks associated with adopting the latest in technology.\r\n\r\nBy leveraging on our investments in technology and infrastructure, businesses will be able to focus on executing their Internet Strategy and no longer need to worry about the high costs and risks of technology implementation.\r\n\r\nWhat do We Do?\r\n\r\ne-Komoditi is a business-to-business e-Commerce infrastructure provider, delivering e-Marketplace, e-Supply and Enterprise Purchasing solutions to mid-large organizations and the government agencies.\r\n\r\ne-Komoditi also provide Application Hosting Services and Comprehensive Integration Services to enable our customers to implement e-commerce within their organizations in an efficient and cost-effective manner.\r\n\r\nOur Key Strategic Partner\r\n\r\nOur strategic alliance with one of the world''s leading e-Commerce technology companies, Qvalent, will also give customers the competitive edge in this new electronic trading field. Formerly known as Metiom Australasia, Qvalent is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Westpac Banking Corporation of Australia. Visit http://www.qvalent.com\r\n\r\nThe solutions provided by Qvalent is proven and companies that have benefited from these solutions include:\r\n\r\nWestpac Ban