(228, 'FEDERATION OF MALAYSIAN MANUFACTURERS', 'FMM - "The Voice of the Malaysian Manufacturing Industry"\r\n\r\nThe Federation of Malaysian Manufacturers (FMM) is Malaysia''s premier economic organisation. Since its establishment in 1968, the FMM has consistently led Malaysian manufacturers in spearheading the nation''s growth and modernisation.\r\n\r\nToday, as the largest private sector economic organisation in Malaysia representing over 2,500 manufacturing and in-dustrial service companies of varying sizes, the FMM is the officially recognised and acknowledged voice of the industry.\r\n\r\nFMM Vision\r\nMaking Malaysian Industries Globally Competitive.\r\n\r\nQuality Policy\r\nTotal commitment to service excellence and quality.\r\n\r\nFMM Perak was formed in 1968 with the objective to provide closer services to members and to look into the development of the local industries. FMM Perak started off with a membership strength of only 20 members. Over its 43 years, membership has been increasing and as of to-date, the Branch is representing over 275 members in Perak.\r\n\r\n\r\nFMM Peraks close liaison with various important State Government Departments and Agencies as well as privatized bodies, is testimony of the State Governments recognition of the FMM as its major partner in the Malaysia Incorporated Concept.\r\n\r\nEstablished to offer a wide range of services and activities to facilitate business operations, we are an important focal point for those seeking links with Malaysian Manufacturers or investment, trade and services. Committed to quality and service excellence, FMM is an ISO 9001 : 2008 certified company and is the leading economic and trade organization in the State.', 125, '	Perak Branch No. 1, Lorong Raja Dihilir, Off Jalan Raja Dihilir, 30350 Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan.', '05-548 8660', 'fmmperak@fmm.org.my', 'http://www.fmm.org.my', 'September-5-2012-4-54-pm-fmm.png', 0, 5105),
