(233, 'Altair Engineering Sdn Bhd', 'A leading global provider of technology that strengthens client innovation\r\n\r\nAltair empowers client innovation and decision-making through technology that optimizes the analysis, management and visualization of business and engineering information. \r\n\r\nPrivately held with more than 1,500 employees, Altair has offices throughout North America, South America, Europe and Asia/Pacific. \r\n\r\nWith a 26-year-plus track record for product design, advanced engineering software, on-demand computing technologies and enterprise analytics solutions, Altair consistently delivers a competitive advantage to more than 3,000 corporate clients representing the automotive, aerospace, government and defense, and consumer products verticals. Altair also has a growing client presence in the life sciences, financial services and energy markets.\r\n\r\nAltair empowers client innovation and decision-making through technology that optimizes the analysis, management and visualization of business and engineering information. Privately held with more than 1,500 employees, Altair has offices throughout North America, South America, Europe and Asia/Pacific. With a 26-year-plus track record for high-end software for engineering and computing, enterprise analytics solutions, and innovative product design and development, Altair has more than 3,000 corporate clients representing the automotive, aerospace, government and defense, and consumer products verticals. Altair also has a growing client presence in the life sciences, financial services and energy markets.\r\n\r\nAt Altair, people are its greatest resource. Highly skilled and diverse in industry experience, Altair''s world-class staff of engineers and design consultants share a high level of technical education and in-depth knowledge of products and processes.\r\n\r\nWe have established our position as an industry leader by selecting the best and brightest people around. A "people" oriented organization, Altair can be described as "entrepreneurial," with an intense focus on innovation.\r\n\r\nWe are always seeking experienced personnel with exceptional educational and technical backgrounds, particularly in aerospace engineering, civil engineering, electrical engineering, mechanical engineering, communications, marketing, sales, software development, and software product support.', 82, 'Suite#1629 Regus, Level 16, 1Sentral, Jalan Stesen Sentral 5, KL Sentral, 50470 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.', '03-20929287', 'srirangam.srirangarajan@altair.com', 'http://www.altair.com/', 'September-6-2012-12-03-pm-altair.jpg', 0, 5117),
(234, 'Symphony BPO Solutions Sdn Bhd', 'The Symphony family comprised of diverse cultures and nationalities such as Malaysians, Australians, Europeans, Indians, Taiwanese, Japanese and Koreans. We have grown to a stronger 1,500 headcount and counting, including our overseas staff in Osaka, Japan and Pune, India. We continue to instill in our employees a strong message on our aspiration to be Employer of Choice by developing a global ready and socially aware workforce.\r\n\r\nWork Culture\r\n\r\nWe are a strong believer in the balance between work and play. Our landmark office building in Ara Damansara offers a healthy competitive work environment with its 6,000 sq ft Rest & Relax hall equipped with Pool Tables, Foosball Tables, Mini Theatre, Reading Corner and Internet Kiosks. Aerobics, Yoga and Body Combat classes are conducted weekly at the state-of-the-art Gym & Dance Studio, complete with Shower Stalls and Locker Rooms.\r\n\r\nReward & Recognition\r\n\r\nAs a major player in the Business Process Outsourcing industry, our main asset is our PEOPLE. We recognize and reward our high performers and long-serving employees via our Symphony Employee Appreciation Awards and Symphony Long Service Awards.\r\n\r\nLearning Development\r\n\r\nSymphony Internship Programme\r\nSymphony Management Trainee Programme\r\nNew Hire Orientation Programme\r\nJob Opportunity Programme + 1\r\nSkills Enhancement Programmes  Internal/External\r\n\r\nCorporate Profile\r\n\r\nThe Symphony Group is one of Asias leading business process outsourcing (BPO) outfit and the partner of choice for more than 3,000 clients  from private and public-listed companies to Fortune 500, Global 500 and large conglomerates across the Asia Pacific region. We are a top 100 Global Offshoring Company and the only Malaysian Company to be named for three consecutive years in the Global Services 100 list, an annual study recognising excellence among global service providers published by Global Services/neoIT.\r\n\r\nThe parent company, Symphony House Berhad, was successfully listed on the MESDAQ Market of Bursa Securities Exchange (then known as the Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange) on 14 February 2003 and two years later, leapt-frog to the Main Board of the Bursa Securities exchange on 1 September 2005. Symphony House Berhad was ranked 5th in the Corporate Governance Survey 2007 carried out by the Minority Shareholder Watchdog Group (MSWG) in collaboration with Nottingham University Business School.\r\n\r\nWe operate out of several locations in Malaysia, Osaka, Japan and Bangalore, India delivering Contact Management, Human Resource, Financial, Corporate Secretarial, Share Issuance and Registration and Cheque Processing Solutions. We also develop and implement Wealth Management Software Solutions for financial institutions in Malaysia and the region.', 97, 'Level 5, Symphony House Pusat Dagangan Dana 1, Jalan PJU 1A/46 47301 Petaling Jaya Selangor Darul Ehsan Malays', '03-7841 800', 'muhammad.imran@symphony.com.my', 'http://www.symphony.com.my', 'September-6-2012-12-33-pm-symphony.gif', 0, 5118),
(235, 'Country Heights Holdings Berhad', 'Country Heights Holdings Berhad (CHHB) is a fast growing and diversified public listed company with interests in property development & investment, luxury estates, golf courses to event planning, exhibition and timeshare. As a dynamic and rapidly expanding company, we seek enthusiastic and committed individuals with a passion for success to join and grow with our team, At CHHB, we are committed to making your life better!\r\n \r\nBenefits\r\nAt CHHB, our employees enjoy a competitive and attractive remuneration package. This includes benefits such as meal and transport allowance, group and medical insurance plus performance based bonuses as well as a 5-day work week.\r\n \r\nLearning and Growth\r\nBut thats not all, if youre looking for an exciting and challenging work environment, this is it. You will learn and grow from working with a diversified group of professionals.\r\nPlease review the Job Opportunities. If there are no opportunities deemed available or suitable, please submit your resume as a general application.  \r\n\r\nDEPOSIT RESUME', 44, 'COUNTRY HEIGHTS HOLDINGS BERHAD 10th Floor, Block C, Mines Waterfront Business Park  No. 3, Jalan Tasik, Mines Resort City,  43300 Seri Kembangan, Selangor Darul Ehsan ', '603-8943 88', 'linda@countryheights.com.my', 'http://www.countryheights.com.my', 'September-6-2012-3-18-pm-CountryHeight.jpg', 0, 5120),
(236, 'Parkson Corporation Sdn Bhd', '	\r\n\r\nProfile\r\nFoundations of a local retail empire (Malaysia)\r\n\r\nEstablished in 1987, Parkson Corporation Sdn Bhd  the retailing arm of the Lion Group rapidly became one of the largest retail chains in Malaysia.\r\n\r\n \r\n 	\r\n\r\nOur department stores\r\n\r\nIn the department store sector, Parkson has strategically tiered its stores to cater to the needs of different market segments and locations. No confusion as the stores are categorized into 3 tiers depending on suitability of market & location.\r\n\r\n	\r\nPremium stores such as Parkson Pavilion, KLCC, 1 Utama and Gurney Plaza bring a whole new store environment with contemporary retail presentation, open walkways, chic displays and vibrant lighting, creating a cozy ambience that pampers customers and enhances their overall shopping experience. Housed with  designers and international labels, it has garnered unbelievable responses amongst the fashion crowd and attracted more discerning shoppers to the store.\r\nOthers Parkson Department Stores, offers a more lifestyle selection of merchandise focused on style, quality and variety, in a contemporary ambience targeting the middle and upper income families.\r\n\r\nTo date Parkson own and operate 38 stores nationwide (west & East Malaysia).\r\n\r\n	\r\nParkson outside Malaysia\r\nParkson China\r\nIn 1994, Parkson China (Parkson) opened its first department store in Beijing, positioning itself at the middle and middle-upper end of the retail market of the Peoples Republic of China (PRC). Parkson is one of the first foreign department store chains to establish a presence in PRC. Todate, it is one of the premier retail operators in PRC having an extensive network of department stores covering 26 major cities in 18 provinces across PRC. \r\n\r\nParkson is a renowned foreign brand with strong brand recognition focusing on fashion and lifestyle among the middle and middle upper class consumers. Over the years, Parkson has developed well-established relationships with various distinguished international and PRC domestic brands, allowing Parkson to offer a wide range of merchandise in its stores. This also enables Parkson to develop its image in the minds of the consumers and maintain its status as one of the leading retail department stores in PRC.\r\n\r\nParkson Vietnam\r\nThe opening of Parkson Saigontourist Plaza on June 29, 2005, marked the entrance of Parkson as the leading department store in Asia and the first truly international department store to be opened in Ho Chi Minh City. \r\nThroughout our store, consumers can find well-known international fashion brands that have never been distributed in Vietnam before including Porsche Design, Eternity, Sub Jeans, Soda Exchange, Baleno for apparels, Armani, DKNY, Tommy Hilfiger for cosmetics and fragrances. Favorite Vietnamese brands such as WOW, Nguyen Jenny and Donga Silk can also be found at Parkson, creating a booming retail hub right in the heart of Ho Chi Minh City.\r\n\r\nParkson Saigontourist Plaza also provides direct and indirect local employment for over 1000 employees.\r\n\r\nMoving Forward\r\n\r\nAs a store that prides itself as the Malaysian department store that constantly stays true to the needs and aspirations of the people, we will continues to evolve in order to stay relevant. Catering to the emergence of new-age consumers who are well traveled, brand/image conscious and lifestyle-oriented are key considerations that drive the PARKSON brand strategy.\r\n\r\nStaying on the pulse of shopping trends, PARKSON will continue to offers a complete shopping experience that combines a line-up of international brands whilst maintaining the choice of variety that suits different tastes and styles of its discerning customers and we look forward to grow with Malaysia for many more years to come. \r\n\r\n \r\n 	 ', 47, 'Parkson Corporation Sdn Bhd   \r\nLevel 5, Klang Parade,\r\n2112, Jalan Meru,\r\n41050 Klang,\r\nSelangor Darul Ehsan,\r\nMalaysia', '03-33442882', 'mohdshah@parkson.com.my', 'http://www.parkson.my', 'September-6-2012-4-08-pm-parkson.jpg', 0, 5126),
(237, 'Gardenia Bakeries (KL) Sdn Bhd', 'About Us\r\n\r\nGardenia Bakeries (KL) Sdn Bhd (GBKL) is a subsidiary of a food listed company, QAF Ltd, who also operates Gardenia Singapore, Gardenia Philippines and will soon be opening Gardenia bakery in Fujian, China.\r\n\r\nGBKL is an associate company of Padi Beras Nasional Berhad.\r\n\r\nBrief History\r\n\r\nIn 1969, an American named Horatio Sye Slocumm was sent by International Executive Service Corporation (IESC) to East Malaysia to start a bakery. Mr. Slocumm brought with him 35 years of baking experience with one of America''s leading chain of bakeries. Gardenia was born.\r\n\r\nGardenia Bakeries (KL) Sdn Bhd rolled the first loaf of bread off its line in 1986. Within four short years, it became the bread market leader with an astounding 99 percent brand recall rate and 80 percent top-of-mind recall.\r\n\r\nGardenia''s range of products grew and evolved through the years, becoming better and better with each step. Leveraging on its brand strength, Gardenia now produces a variety of baked products to satisfy consumers'' demands.\r\n\r\n', 1, 'Lot 3, Jalan Pelabur 23/1, 40300 Shah Alam, Selangor Darul Ehsan Malaysia', '03-55423228', 'customer_service@gardenia.com.my', 'http://www.gardenia.com.my', 'September-7-2012-5-08-pm-Gardenia-Bakeries-(KL)-Sdn-Bhd.jpg', 0, 5130),
(238, 'Munchy Food Industries Sdn. Bhd.', 'It all started in 1991, in a small peaceful town down south of Malaysia. Our biscuit connoisseurs grew up on the heavenly smells of freshly-baked handmade biscuits that constantly filled their fathers biscuit factory.\r\n\r\nAffectionately known as their second home, it was there that they lived, ate, slept, studied and played. During the school holidays, they helped make and pack biscuits, and would quite happily follow Dad everywhere. \r\n\r\nWhile growing up in a biscuit factory sounds like a childs dream come true, life wasnt always all fun and games (unlike a Munchys biscuit thats fun and games, all day and all night long!). Many biscuits and wafers were burnt, broken and bruised along the way. But their hard work paid off, as they amassed secrets learnt from their forefathers (to be used in the future with the birth of Munchys) to make the perfect homemade biscuit  handmade with cheeky fun, laughter, and above all, love.\r\n\r\nWhile the magic of Munchys started with one second-hand wafer stick machine worth RM80,000, many trials and tribulations were faced along the way. Their sole machine broke down many a time, yet it did not break their spirits. They would fix it each time, and lo and behold, it would start producing lip-smacking biscuits once again. And when things got better, the brothers began purchasing more equipment directly from machine manufacturers so that they could assemble the machines in the most innovative and productive ways possible. \r\n\r\nSoon enough, their production capacity increased as they worked towards their dream  and that was to share the joys of Munchys with the rest of the world. The first destination? South Africa. Their biscuits were welcomed with open arms (and mouths), and everybody kept asking for more. Subsequently, they tied up with a reputable MNC chocolate company that allowed them to extend their Munchys goodness to chocolate wafers. \r\n\r\nAs the years went by and business thrived, the name Munchys began to gain popularity amongst biscuit lovers. From Malaysias local shores to over the seas, the name Munchys caused many hungry tummies to squeal excitedly. Evolving from an Original Equipment Manufacturer to a household name, this meant that they also had the key ingredients and knowledge to build the brand name and brand affinity, thus creating the irresistible brand known as Munchys, which was born in 1993.\r\n\r\nThe following year saw the introduction of MunchWorld Marketing Sdn Bhd, Munchys marketing arm and sole distributor of Munchys products, as well as other leading FMCG brands. MunchWorld Marketing Sdn Bhd. This entity was set up as a power house to spearhead Munchys branding, marketing, advertising, events, promotions and distribution of all things Munchys. The launch of MunchWorld Marketing kicked off with a big bang in all three of its nationwide offices, simultaneously.\r\n\r\n\r\nOne of the key ingredients of Munchys success is the hard work and dedication shown by each and every one of Munchys employees.\r\n\r\nToday, Munchys is backed by 1,200 fulltime employees and more than 300 creative marketers and sales gurus who help spread the goodness of Munchys all over the world. \r\n\r\nThe sky is truly the limit for Munchys. With the perfect mix of innovation and achievements, its only a matter of time before the whole wide world gets to sink their teeth into a Munchys treat.\r\n\r\nAt Munchys, we believe that our people are like the best parts of a Munchys treat. Chocolate chips, creamy wafers, crunchy nutseach and every employee is an essential player in making Munchys the awesomest biscuit in town.\r\n\r\nWe also believe that our work environment should be a growing pool of talent, where we develop and build upon each others strengths to create and maintain our playground of ideas and help one another achieve our full potential. \r\n', 37, 'MunchWorld Marketing Sdn. Bhd.  70A, Laluan Perajurit Satu, Taman Ipoh Timur, Ipoh 31350 Perak, Malaysia.', '05 - 547708', 'munchys@munchys.com', 'http://www.munchys.com', 'September-10-2012-11-43-am-munchy-logo.jpg', 0, 5154),
(239, 'Secret Recipe Cakes & Cafe Sdn Bhd', 'Founded in 1997, Secret Recipe made its mark, renowned for its extensive range of fine quality gourmet cakes. It has since evolved to become one of the fastest growing lifestyle cakes and caf chain in the region with over 280 caf outlets to date.\r\nSecret Recipe Cakes & Caf''s concept can be found in prime urban locations and shopping malls in major cities in the region including Singapore, Kuala Lumpur, Jakarta, Bangkok, Manila, Brunei, Shanghai and Melbourne.\r\n\r\nSecret Recipe promises a value lifestyle proposition of great variety and quality food at affordable prices. The uncompromising quality of food and desserts using quality ingredients, coupled with moderate pricing, has created a new lifestyle cult, compromising of a loyal base of food and cake lovers.\r\n\r\nSecret Recipe Cakes & Caf offers a friendly and personalised full-service dining experience for customers and incorporates a modern contemporary and vibrant interior concept with comfort ambience, and great food. It provides a great respite for customers to enjoy good food and quality time with friends, family or associates, after a long day at work.', 24, ' SECRET RECIPE CAKES & CAFE SDN BHD (467990-X) 42, Jalan SS25/28, 47301 Petaling Jaya, Selangor Darul Ehsan, Malaysia.', '03-7806 155', 'recruitment@secretrecipe.com.my', 'http://www.secretrecipe.com.my', 'September-10-2012-12-14-pm-secret-recipe.gif', 0, 5162),
(240, 'The Syuen', 'Hotel management and hospitality', 1, 'The Syuen, 88, Jalan Sultan Abdul Jalil, 30300 Ipoh, Perak Darul Ridzuan. West Malaysia.', '05-22538889', 'admin@syuenhotel.com.my', 'http://www.syuenhotel.com.my', 'September-10-2012-12-42-pm-syuen.jpg', 0, 5168),
(241, 'Axieara Farm (IP0361726  H)', ' Menjual ternakan hidup ( Lembu, Kerbau dan Kambing ). Mengeluar & menjual Baja Kompos. Menyediakan kemudahan Contract Farming. Memproses & Membekal makanan ternakan\r\n\r\nMenyedari bidang penternakan adalah satu perniagaan yang menguntungkan dan mampu memenuhi hasrat kerajaan untuk menjadikan industri ini sebagai salah satu sumber ekonomi utama negara pada masa hadapan, syarikat kami telah merancang, menambah baik dan akan melaksanakan strategi pemasaran dengan cara yang lebih bersistematik dan berkesan bagi memperluaskan lagi industri penternakan lembu memandangkan permintaan terhadap lembu hidup dan daging segar yang semakin meningkat dari semasa ke semasa. ', 4, 'NO. 2A, MEDAN ISTANA 2 BANDAR IPOH RAYA 30000 IPOH PERAK DARUL RIDZUAN.', ' 05  249', 'axiearafarm@gmail.com', 'http://axiearafarms.blogspot.com/', 'September-10-2012-12-55-pm-logofarm.jpg', 0, 5171),
(242, 'Kinta Riverfront Hotel & Suites Sdn. Bhd', 'hotel / hospitality\r\n\r\nCommenced on 1st January 2012, Kinta Riverfront Hotel & Suite is one of the latest luxury destinations for holiday retreats in Ipoh. Strategically located in the centre of Ipoh city, it lies elegantly along the Kinta River and runs parallel with Jalan Lim Bo Seng. It is owned by the Morubina Group of Companies whom are the owners of Hillcity Hotel & Condo Ipoh.\r\n\r\nWe proudly announce that our hotel is the pioneer of few trendy facilities. The Mermaid Pool & Bar is the longest and transparent see-through glass swimming pool in Perak which is beyond question the best spot for cocktail, theme party and wedding...', 31, ' Kinta Riverfront Hotel & Suites Sdn. Bhd Jalan Lim Bo Seng, 30000 Ipoh, Perak', '05-245 8888', 'sales@kintariverfront.com.my', 'http://www.kintariverfront.com.my', 'September-10-2012-3-14-pm-kinta.jpg', 0, 5174),
(243, 'Appco Group Malaysia', 'Appco Group Malaysia is part of The Appco Group, which has more than 800 locations in 26 countries making Appco one of the most progressive direct sales and marketing companies in the world.\r\n\r\nThe Appco Group represents and sells products and services on behalf of blue chip companies. Every day we reach and speak to more than one million people and generate hundreds and thousands of new customers.\r\n\r\nThe range of products and services the Appco Group represent includes telecommunications, pay TV, broadband, insurance, fundraising and energy just to name a few.\r\n\r\nAppco''s success comes down to its investment in people and developing a world-class and industry-leading sales coaching system, territory management, campaign management, product development, quality assurance programs and state-of-the-art post-sales processing centres.\r\n', 104, 'Level 18, Quill 7, No. 9, Jalan Sentral, Kuala Lumpur Sentral, 50470 Kuala Lumpur,  Malaysia', '03 2262 230', 'joanne@appcogroup.asia', 'http://news.appcogroupmalaysia.com', 'September-10-2012-3-26-pm-AppcogroupMalaysia.jpg', 0, 5175),
(244, 'Multi-Trans Sdn Bhd', 'Multi-Trans aims to:-\r\n\r\nmeet customers'' requirement of safety, effectiveness and timely execution of services by adhering to professional standard working procedures.\r\n\r\nconstantly improve its services by upgrading facilities, human resources, teamwork, network, communication, technology and methodology.\r\n\r\ncreate a happy working environment where all staff are motivated, service driven, disciplined, well trained and team players.\r\n\r\nexpand further domestically and internationally by achieving bigger market share, covering new geographical areas and venturing into new products and services, thus ensuring a leading and respectable position in the industry as international freight forwarding and total logistics service provider in Malaysia and the region.', 56, '197 & 199, Persiaran Raja Muda Musa,  42000 Port Klang,  Selangor, Malaysia.', '03-3375 228', 'hrm@multi-trans.com.my', 'http://www.multi-trans.com.my', 'September-10-2012-3-39-pm-multi.gif', 0, 5176),
(245, 'Suruhanjaya Sekuriti', 'The SC recognises that the quality of human resource is key to developing and regulating a complex and dynamic industry. Our staff derive considerable satisfaction from working in a respected, high-profile public agency that looks after public interest. They belief strongly in our mandate of protecting investors and ensuring the transparency, integrity and orderly development of the Malaysian capital market which makes their work meaningful.\r\n\r\nOur human resource policy is aimed at developing capable professionals, specialists, experts and managerial talent that will drive results and advance the organisation''s objectives. Our talent pool comes from a diversity of fields that include accounting, economics, law, mathematics, business studies, information technology, engineering, science, philosophy and languages.\r\n\r\nOur employees are constantly challenged to learn and evolve their skill sets to map or even be ahead of the continuous changing financial landscape. The SC employee is loyal, committed, articulate, professional, and balanced in perspective and approach.\r\n \r\nOn its part, the SC works towards ensuring an ideal environment where people can contribute. Through various programmes, the SC employee can gain breadth and depth of experience, hone their technical skills, and as they advance in the organisation, ample opportunities are provided to test their management and leadership competence.\r\n \r\nThe SC is committed to be an "Employer of Choice". We recognise the importance of balancing one''s career with one''s pursuit of a personal life.', 52, 'Professional Education & Services  Securities Industry Development Corporation No 3, Persiaran Bukit Kiara  Bukit Kiara  50490 Kuala Lumpur', ' 603-6204 8', ' sidc@sidc.com.my', 'http://www.sc.com.my', 'September-10-2012-5-43-pm-Sc.gif', 0, 5179),
(246, 'Toshiba Electronics Malaysia Sdn Bhd', 'Toshiba is a manufacturing company which produce semiconductor such as Integrated Circuit and Discrete for overseas business.', 37, 'KM15 Jalan Klang Banting, Telok Panglima Garang, 42507 Kuala Langat, Selangor', '03-31226001', 'recruit@tem.toshiba.co.jp', 'na', 'default_employ.png', 0, 5183),
(247, 'Malay-Sino Chemical Industries Sdn Bhd ', 'We are a subsidiary of the Batu Kawan Berhad Group of Companies, a public listed company on the Main Board of the KLSE, with 4 manufacturing facilities in the country.  We are the largest manufacturer of chlor-alkali products in the industry and an ISO 9001:2000 accredited company.  We have, for more than 30 years at Malay-Sino Chemical Industries Sdn Bhd, strived to maintain our pioneering and caring approach to become a reliable supplier to our customers and a trusted employer to our loyal employees.  As we continue to strive for excellence, we are looking for motivated and performance-oriented individuals to join our team based in Lahat, Ipoh:', 12, '4 1/2 Miles, Jalan Lahat 30200 Ipoh, Perak ', '05- 3224255', ' aachong@malay-sino.com.my', 'http://www.malay-sino.com.my', 'September-11-2012-10-00-am-msci.gif', 0, 5184),
(248, 'First-Linen Products Sdn Bhd', 'Our Story\r\n\r\nFirst Linen Products Sdn Bhd Are incorporated in 1990. Being a wholesaler distributor of bedlinen products such as bedsheet, comforter, while quilt cover, pillow and bolster case, mattress pad and cushion cover.\r\n\r\nWindsir is a locally recognized name and our merchandise is available through more than 120 retail outlets in Malaysia.\r\nOur Service\r\n\r\nWe cater for all who are interested in our range of products in general, hotels and institutions projects alike. Quotation, sizes, quantities and qualities are subjected to negotiations with prospective clients.\r\nOur Products\r\n\r\nBed Sheet\r\nPillow Case, Bolster Case,\r\nDuvet Cover, While Quilt, Comforter\r\nMattress & Pillow Protector, Pillow, Bolster, Aroma Pillow, Memory Foam\r\nScatter Cushion, Floor Cushion, Curtain ', 37, '2,Hala Rapat Baru 23, Jalan Gopeng Kawasan Perindustrian Ringan Kinta Jaya Ipoh', '05 - 311133', 'hrd@windsir.com.my', 'http://www.windsir.com.my', 'September-11-2012-10-12-am-top-banner-logo.jpg', 0, 5185),
(249, 'Power Root (M) Sdn Bhd', 'POWER ROOT (M) SDN. BHD. was founded on 23 July 1999 in Johor Bahru, Johor. It is a leading company to develop and promote herbal energy drinks fortified with two main rainforest herbs: Eurycoma longifolia Jack or commonly known as "Tongkat Ali" and Labisia Pumilia and Pathoina or "Kacip Fatimah". These herbs are indigenous to Malaysia and its properties for promoting physical well-being are highly regarded by Malaysians.\r\n\r\nPOWER ROOT (M) SDN. BHD. is now a subsidiary of a public listed company: POWER ROOT BERHAD (formerly known as Natural Bio Resources Berhad), a company listed on the Main Market of Bursa Malaysia Securities Berhad. \r\n\r\nWith the determination to promote these local products in the international markets, Power Root has invested heavily in research and development of these traditional herbs to create its own brand of products. \r\n\r\n\r\nIn March 2001, Power Root established a marketing branch in Kuala Lumpur to better coordinate its logistic and serve its customers more effectively. \r\n\r\nIn 2003, Power Root started its very own manufacturing plant in Johor Bahru to cater for growing demands. An 18-acre phase 1 manufacturing facility is expected to be completed early 2008, incorporating modern production technology to cater for the strong market demand locally, business development opportunities abroad and new formulations development.\r\n\r\nPower Root with its entrepreneur spirit, is committed to provide consumers with the ultimate choice of a high quality product. Concentrated efforts in research and development to develop new and improve existing products have also accelerated its success in the market. As such, the company was able to quickly establish a stable business foundation and thus, creates a very promising future for the company.\r\n\r\n', 104, 'No.1, Jalan Sri Plentong, Taman Perindustrian Sri Plentong, 81750 Masai,  Johor Darul Takzim, Malaysia.', '07 - 386 68', ' sales@powerroot.com.my', 'http://www.powerroot.com.my', 'September-11-2012-10-41-am-poweroot.png', 0, 5187),
(250, 'Kurz Production (Malaysia) Sdn Bhd', 'The KURZ group is the international market leader in hot stamping technology. The headquarters is located in Germany. With over 2,500 employees in 9 production facilities world-wide and 16 international branch offices, we excel in the manufacturing and distribution of quality products for application tecnology in the decorative and security industry.', 37, 'Lot 22, Seri Iskandar Technology Park, Bota Perak.', '05-3745023', 'faridah.shariff@Kurz.com.my', NULL, 'September-11-2012-10-43-am-kpm-logo.bmp', 0, 5189),
(251, 'IKHTIAR MENARA SDN BHD', '-', 15, 'No. 624A, Jalan Sempadan, Simpang Empat, PARIT BUNTAR', '05 - 716676', 'imsb_624@yahoo.com', '-', 'default_employ.png', 0, 5190),
(252, 'TCIM SDN BHD', ' 	\r\n\r\nA PHILOSOPHY of DEPENDABILITY\r\n\r\nOur corporate philosophy is customer focused. The reason is simple. Since 1983 we have supplied material handling, agricultural, construction and power generation equipment to a variety of sectors. Our customers demand support services equal to the quality of the international product range that we represent. We have gained their trust and confidence by being responsive to their expectations. This has made us Malaysia''s leading name in equipment sales and services.\r\n\r\n\r\nGeared for EFFICIENCY\r\n\r\nCustomer confidence is critical. At TCIM we commit our entire capabilities into achieving this. Our nationwide network and highly trained technical staff make it possible for us to provide the best possible after sales support at all times. TCIM technical staffs attend various training sessions, refresher courses and development seminars. To our customers this means faster response and shorter equipment downtime.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe''re About SOLUTIONS\r\n\r\nBe it equipment or services, TCIM is solution oriented. We represent some of the most respected brands in the world. This allows us to offer the best equipment for a wide variety of applications. What''s more, we put our Total Commitment Support behind every piece of equipment we supply. From the simplest to the most complex machinery, we are staffed and equipped to quickly solve service, maintenance and parts demands of every kind.\r\n\r\n\r\nAIMS & OBJECTIVES\r\n\r\nHere in Malaysia, TCIM aims to craft a crystal like reputation among the most respected customers globally worldwide. We aim to establish TCIM and be recognised as a brand rather than just being a distributor itself. We want to change a customer''s mindset on how they treat us as a brand. We feel very confident in our achivements so far and there''s still a long journey ahead to the grand prize.', 30, 'Lot 9, Jalan Delima 1/1 Subang Hi-Tech Industrial Park 40000 Shah Alam, Selangor D E', '03-5621 178', 'hblu@tcim.com.my', 'http://www.tcim.com.my', 'September-11-2012-11-52-am-logo_tcim.jpg', 0, 5191),
(253, 'SN Low & Associates Sdn Bhd ', 'Being independently structured and at the same time forming part of a larger corporate group affords us opportunities and value adding expertise that we have to offer our clients. Our guiding principle of generating products which pushes beyond boundaries in the dynamics of a fluid environment always distinguishes our projects in the marketplace. The focus and objectives of our organisation is to achieve creativity for our clients who has to deal with more uncertainties in a world of continuous change except for the bottom line. In the new millennium, a successful relationship has already crossed the client consultant divide into a smart partnership with a common vision. The global reach is already here to stay and our intention is to be there with you. ', 6, 'No. 63, Jln Ss15/4b, 47500 Petaling Jaya, Selangor', '03-5632 354', 'hr@acasysgroup.com', 'www.snla.com.my', 'September-11-2012-12-43-pm-logo.jpg', 0, 5193),
(254, 'POPULAR BOOK CO. (M) SDN BHD', 'Founded in 1924 and listed on the Singapore Stock Exchange, we are an established brand with a wide network and strong market share in the Malaysia retail scene. Our core businesses are in retailing, publishing, distribution and we are now moving into a new business segment i.e. e-learning. Our global operations span across Singapore, Malaysia, Hong Kong, Macau, China, Taiwan, United Kingdom and Canada. We have maintained our competitive edge by continually striving towards better business practices and strengthening our commitment to serve our customers in the best possible way.', 47, 'No. 8, Jalan 7/118B Desa Tun Razak 56000 Kuala Lumpur', '03-9179 600', 'recruitment@popularworld.com', '-', 'September-11-2012-1-06-pm-popular.jpg', 0, 5194),
(255, 'Trapia Malaysia Sdn Bhd', 'Trapia is marking 3 years of producing tilapia in the pristine waters of Lake Temenggor surrounded by the lush green forest environment. During these three years, Trapia has already become one of the leading producers when it comes to sustainability and compliance with leading seafood standards', 4, 'No 2, Jalan Taman Kinta Chateau Garden, 30250 Ipoh, Perak', '05 - 255 19', 'trapia.enquiry@gmail.com', 'http://www.trapia.com.my/', 'September-11-2012-2-15-pm-9079516.jpg', 0, 5195),
(256, 'Watson ', 'Watsons Personal Care Stores (Malaysia) Sdn Bhd. is part of the Health and Beauty Store chain of A.S Watson, the largest health, beauty, cosmetics, and perfumery retailer in the world. Today, Watsons H&B Asia is the leading health and beauty chain in the continent with successful operations in 9 markets (Hong Kong, China, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, Indonesia, Korea, Taiwan, and the Philippines). \r\n\r\nIn 1994, Watsons Malaysia opened its first outlet in Holiday Plaza, Johor Bahru. In 2005, Watsons successfully acquired the Apex Pharmacy chain, in which consists of 18 stores nationwide. This significant milestone brought Watsons to a higher level in the pharmacy business. Today, Watsons operates over 250 stores in Malaysia serving more than 50,000 customers per day. \r\n\r\nWatsons strives to live up to customers'' expectations through marketing campaigns, a wide variety of high quality merchandise at great value and provides an exciting shopping experience. The wide range of merchandise also encompasses competitively priced house brand and private label products.\r\n\r\nWith more than 1000 brands ranging from medicines, health supplements, skin care, toiletries and cosmetics, Watsons Your Personal Store is your one-stop Health, Wellness and Beauty solution centre.\r\n\r\nThe Watson''s culture is fast-paced and energetic. It is a supportive environment where talented people are given real responsibility and the opportunity to succeed. If you have the talent and the ambition,come and join "the Watsons team" to fulfill your true potential.', 106, 'LOT F7 1ST FLR KINTA CITY SHPG CTR, JLN THE LEAN SWEE, IPOH GARDEN, 34100 IPOH', '-', 'mywatsons@watsons.com.my', 'http://www.watsons.com.my', 'September-11-2012-2-25-pm-WTSN.png', 0, 5196),
(257, 'Sunborn Marine Malaysia Sdn Bhd', 'Sunborn Marine Malaysia Sdn Bhd a part of Sunborn Group - company specialized in building and operating luxury hotels in Europe - is now looking for well motivated Malaysian citizens to join its project team in Lumut. Now company is expanding Malaysian operations, and is looking for qualified personnel for this position. Persons with preferable experienced in shipbuilding or construction are preferred.', 15, ' No. 43-45 Lumut Pantai Impian, 32200 Lumut, Perak', '05 - 683 63', 'fazilah.zainal@sunbornmarine.com   ', 'http://www.sunborn.com/', 'September-11-2012-2-43-pm-logo.jpg', 0, 5197),
(258, 'Baskin Robbins Malaysia', 'Do you love ice cream? Are you looking to work in a fun, exciting and innovative environment? At Baskin-Robbins, we have a passion for delivering irresistible treats, smiles and fun for the entire neighborhood.\r\n\r\nImagine...working for a company that knows the key to success in the marketplace is its people. We are now seeking for individuals who are self-motivated, passionate and team-oriented. If this sounds like you, join us now !\r\n\r\nYou could have the opportunity to develop your interpersonal skills, work on your managerial skills and further your career.', 24, 'Kinta City Shopping Centre, Jalan Teh Lean Swee, Off Jalan Sultan Azlan Shah Utara, 31400 Ipoh, Perak.', '05-5483 031', 'contact@baskinrobbins.com.my', 'http://www.baskinrobbins.com.my', 'September-11-2012-2-54-pm-Baskin-Robbins.jpg', 0, 5198),
(259, 'Double Site Marketing Sdn Bhd', 'We are a new breed in helmet manufacturing inspired by the passion for safety, security and execellent quality. In anticipation of this life-long dream, our exclusive product innovation team do their utmost to provide our valued customers a wide range of innovated helmets satisfying each and every different requirement, category and standard. We are determined to present wholesome helmets offering secured safety, style as well as comfort.\r\n\r\nAll DOUBLE SITE helmets are locally manufactured and Sirim Approved. Our team meticulously follow multiple stringent quality control procedures ensuring the required standard. Final inspection on each and every individual unit to sustain the promised quality. Our product innovation team has been striving over the years and is still costantly sustaining to achieve more breakthroughs and competitiveness in the industry with the incorporation of robotics technology leading into automation and programming.', 37, 'Lot 825, Jalan Sungai Korok, Mukim Jitra, 06000 Jitra, Kedah', '04 - 916 38', 'contact@dsxdot.com', 'http://dsxdot.com/ds/', 'September-11-2012-3-37-pm-images.jpg', 0, 5200),
(260, 'Jatroc Pictures Sdn. Bhd', 'Nur Aishah bt. Ramli', 21, 'No 18A, Tingkat 2, Simpang Pulai Business Centre, Jalan PPSP 4, 31300 Simpang Pulai Perak', '0194260790', 'qis_isyah@yahoo.com.my', 'nil', 'default_employ.png', 0, 5206),
(261, 'AEON CO. (M) BHD', 'AEON CO. (M) BHD. (formerly known as Jaya Jusco Stores Bhd.) is a leading retailer in Malaysia with a total revenue of RM3.73 billion in the financial year ended 31st December 2009. The Company was incorporated on 15 September 1984. AEON CO. (M) BHD. was set up in response to the Malaysian Government''s invitation to AEON Japan to help modernise the retailing industry in Malaysia. The ''JUSCO'' name today is well established among Malaysians as well as foreigners, especially due to its association with the international AEON group of companies.', 47, '3rd Floor, AEON Taman Maluri Shopping Centre, Jalan Jejaka, Taman Maluri, Cheras, 55100 Kuala lumpur', '0123709750', 'mohamad_shazri@aeonretail.com.my', 'http://aeonretail.com.my/', 'September-12-2012-9-59-am-aeon.jpg', 0, 5208),
(262, 'GCH Retail (M) Sdn Bhd', 'In Malaysia, Giant is synonymous with everyday low prices, big variety and great value and recognised for offering the most vibrant, comfortable and complete shopping environment.\r\nGiant, which turned 65 in 2009, pioneered the concept of modern supermarket shopping  buying everyday groceries, fresh produce and fresh foods under one roof and in a hygienic environment. As the pioneer, Giant sets the pace and standards for the industry with innovative marketing, store design and product pricing and variety.\r\n', 47, 'Lot 1, Jalan Pinang D, 18/D, Seksyen 18 Kawasan Perniagaan,  40000 Shah Alam Selangor', '0172503322', 'shahronizar@giant.com.my', 'http://www.giant.com.my/', 'September-12-2012-10-05-am-images.jpg', 0, 5209),
(263, 'ECONSAVE', 'The history of Econsave began from a wooden sundry shop in Port Klang more than 50 years ago. Through years of hard work and perserverance, adapting constantly to the changes in the retail scene, Econsave has emerged as one of the largest retailers in Malaysia', 47, 'Address: Lot 218 & 219, 1 Miles, Jalan Pandamaran,  42000 Pelabuhan Klang,  Selangor Darul Ehsan', '0193394197', 'szecy@econsave.com.my', 'http://www.econsave.com.my', 'September-12-2012-10-11-am-econsave.jpg', 0, 5212),
(264, 'Pharmaniaga Berhad', ' Pharmaniaga is a leading Malaysian integrated healthcare group that is driven by its core businesses namely, generic pharmaceuticals manufacturing and R&D, warehousing and distribution of pharmaceutical and medical products, sales & marketing as well as hospital equipping.\r\n \r\nPharmaniaga has also created a niche in healthcare IT solutions, which forms the backbone of our operations. Poised to take the lead in the Malaysian healthcare industry, we are guided by our philosophy of doing business with a conscience and motivated by our mission of enriching life together. We currently seek individuals with the same integrity and professionalism that share our passion for excellence and providing high quality products and services to be part of Pharmaniaga family.', 10, 'No. 7, Lorong Keluli 1B Kawasan Perindustrian Bukit Raja Selatan Seksyen 7, 40000 Shah Alam Selangor Darul Ehsan', '03 - 3342 9', 'recruitment@pharmaniaga.com', 'www.pharmaniaga.com', 'September-12-2012-10-18-am-_logo_5988_banner_0_4346.jpeg', 0, 5210),
(265, 'Syarikat Bekalan Air Selangor Sdn Bhd', 'Syarikat Bekalan Air Selangor Sdn Bhd or better known as SYABAS was incorporated on 8 July 1996 under the Malaysian Companies Act, 1965 to undertake the privatisation of water supply services in the State of Selangor and the Federal Territories of Kuala Lumpur and Putrajaya (''the Privatisation).\r\n	\r\nSYABAS is an entity specifically incorporated for use as an implementation vehicle in respect to the privatization of the water supply and distribution systems in Selangor and Federal Territories of Kuala Lumpur and Putrajaya.\r\n\r\nSYABAS was appointed by the State and Federal Governments to upgrade and enhance the water supply system and services in the State of Selangor under the Privatisation concept in view of the previous managements financial constraint, ineffective management, poor water quality standards and inconsistent supply of treated water.\r\n	\r\nSYABAS was granted a concession by the Federal Government and the Selangor State Government to manage, operate and distribute quality clean water for a period of thirty years, commencing on 1st January 2005.\r\n	\r\nAs the biggest water concessionaire in Malaysia, SYABAS was developed by a visionary entrepreneur who is backed by a team of professional, dedicated and skillful management with a penchant for innovation in excellent customer services as well as reshaping the landscape of the local utility industry.\r\n	\r\nThe authorized share capital of SYABAS is RM100,000,000.00 comprising 93,449,999 ordinary shares of RM1.00 each, one (1) Golden Share of RM1.00 and 655,000,000 redeemable cumulative preference shares ("RPS") of RM0.01 each, while the paid-up share capital of SYABAS is RM71,550,001.00 comprising 65,000,000 ordinary shares of RM1.00 each, 655,000,000 RPS of RM0.01 each and one (1) Golden Share of RM1.00.\r\n	\r\nThe shareholders of SYABAS are Puncak Niaga Holdings Berhad ("PNHB") holding 70% of the total equity shareholding in SYABAS, 15% equity shareholding held by Kumpulan Darul Ehsan Berhad ("KDEB") and the remaining 15% held by Kumpulan Perangsang Selangor Berhad ("KPS"). The Federal Government ("Government") through the Minister of Finance, Incorporated ("MOF") holds one (1) Golden Share in SYABAS.\r\n	\r\nIt is anticipated that the State of Selangor Darul Ehsan and the Federal Territories of Kuala Lumpur and Putrajaya will continue to be a centre of economic growth and thereby, the water demand in the states would continue to grow steadily. The current situation also provides opportunities for the PNHB Group to enhance the overall efficiency of the water industry in particular to reduce the high non-revenue water losses level and uplift the standard of service.\r\n', 58, 'Syarikat Bekalan Air Selangor Sdn.Bhd 2nd Floor, Head Office,Jalan Pantai Baharu, 59990 Kuala Lumpur', '1-800-88-52', 'recruitment@syabas.com.my', 'http://www.syabas.com.my', 'September-12-2012-10-31-am-Jawatan-Kosong-Syarikat-Bekalan-Air-Selangor-Sdn.-Bhd.-(SYABAS).png', 0, 5213),
(266, 'House Of Healin ', 'Working with us means being part of our team that values professionalism, dynamism and creativity. We believe that our employees drive our continued success and we want people who strive for the best in whatever they do. Our philosophy is moving towards a Culture Of Excellence for our human capital.\r\n\r\nWe are not only looking for competent, qualified contributors, but employees who want to grow personally and professionally throughout their careers with the Company.\r\n\r\nIn our House Of Healin, we also provide attractive remuneration which is aimed to attract, engage, reward and retain world-class employees who work together to support the company''s business objectives, missions and vision.', 18, 'No 1, Jalan Kartunis U1/47 Section U1, Temasya Industrial Park 40150 Shah Alam, Selangor', '03-55695580', 'fiza@healwell.com.my', 'http://www.houseofhealin.com.my', 'September-12-2012-10-35-am-hasdnnk.gif', 0, 5214),
(267, 'Petrosains Sdn Bhd', 'Petrosains Sdn Bhd was incorporated to extend PETRONAS'' commitment as a socially responsible corporate citizen in providing a rich and stimulating environment aimed to enhance science literacy and instill in Malaysians a passion for acquiring scientific knowledge. Petrosains is a Science Discovery Centre that uses a fun and interactive approach to tell the story of the science and technology of the petroleum industry. Its concept and contents revolve specifically around the science of petroleum, yet embrace all the general sciences.\r\n\r\nOne of our key focus areas is the constant development of dynamic, professional and dedicated staff and we hope to achieve this through sound business principles and creative teamwork.\r\n\r\nHistory:\r\nPetrosains humble beginnings was envisioned as a dynamic world-class science discovery centre built in the Twin Towers, with special focus on presenting the science and technology of oil and gas as an entry point to understand the natural and technological world. On 25 March 1999, Petrosains was unveiled to the public, offering 70,000 square feet of space filled with knowledge and opportunities for discovery.\r\nCultures and Values:\r\nPetrosains supports PETRONAS'' culture and practice of life-long learning and we believe this value must be inculcated from the very young. Petrosains is designed to stimulate learning through inquiry, investigation and discovery. Petrosains hopes to provide a safe and supportive environment in which visitors can observe, play, explore, investigate, experiment, create, innovate and to question and wonder at or about natural and human-made worlds. We are building and broadest base possible of curious, observant and skilled Malaysians to encourage more to pursue careers in science, technology, engineering or mathematics.', 19, 'PETRONAS Twin Towers Level 4, Suria KLCC, 50088 Kuala Lumpur.', '03-23318787', ' infopetrosains@petronas.com.my', 'http://www.petrosains.com.my', 'September-12-2012-10-53-am-petrosains1a_02.jpg', 0, 5216),
(268, 'Gas Malaysia Berhad', '	\r\nImportant Notice\r\n \r\nGas Malaysia would like to advise that it does not engage or authorise any on-line employment agency or recruitment portal to act on its behalf. \r\n \r\nThose who wish to seek employment with GAS MALAYSIA are advised to visit http://www.gasmalaysia.com or refer to job vacancy section of local newspaper.\r\n\r\nPlease also take note that Gas Malaysia does not request any payment nor charge any fee for processing job applications. \r\n\r\nGas Malaysia is committed to providing an environment that encourages all employees to advance in their chosen paths while continuously enhancing their talents and skills. As employers, we aim to provide good working conditions, competitive compensation and opportunities for personal development and growth.\r\n\r\nWe are constantly looking for talented, energetic and enthusiastic people to join us and help us achieve our vision and mission as an organisation.\r\n\r\n', 41, 'The Human Resource Department Gas Malaysia Berhad No. 5, Jalan Serendah 26/17 Seksyen 26, Peti Surat 7901 40732 Shah Alam Selangor Darul Ehsan', '-', 'hr@gasmalaysia.com', 'http://www.gasmalaysia.com', 'September-12-2012-11-13-am-gas_logo.jpg', 0, 5218);
