(274, 'OCS Malaysia Kuala Lumpur Head office (Internation', 'Because our global society has recently undergone dramatic change and is becoming increasingly borderless, the amount of information now circulating is truly staggering. That''s why it''s so important to use a \r\ncourier service which can navigate its way through the information maze to deliver business documents and parcels safely, soundly, and rapidly. OCS does this today, just as we have been doing it for more \r\nthan 40 years\r\nWith the cooperation of leading Japanese journalistic organizations, OCS was founded in 1957 as an overseas distributor of Japanese newspapers. Later it became widely recognized primarily as a highly reliable courier service. \r\n\r\nOverseas operations began in offices in San Francisco . Since those early days, we have expanded to such an extent that today OCS serves customers in 77 countries and 231 cities all over the world. The reliability\r\nand speed of our service have earned OCS a high level of trust - not to mention an outstanding reputation - from government offices, trading companies, financial institutions, and a variety of corporations around \r\nthe globe.\r\n\r\nOCS will pick up and deliver a variety of items anywhere in the world. Our document courier service will accept as little as one page, while at the same time ensuring these items such as blueprints, contracts, and business letters get to their destinations on time.\r\nYou can also rest assured that your delicate articles will arrive safely when you use our small package service. CD, video and audio CD, motion picture films, and delicate instruments will be handled with care from start to finish.\r\nOur experienced service professionals will be happy to answer any questions you may have and offer helpful advice when needed. Give OCS a call the next time you decide to send something. Once its in our hands, theres no need to worry.', 56, 'OCS Malaysia Kuala Lumpur Head office (International Courier)No. 20A, Jalan Penchala, 46050 Petaling Jaya, Selangor Darul Ehsan', '03-77811211', 'exportocskul@ocscourier.com.my', 'http://www.ocscourier.com.sg', 'September-12-2012-3-11-pm-OCSLogo2_g.gif', 0, 5238),
(275, 'Eweny Chemicals Sdn Bhd', 'Eweny Chemicals Sdn Bhd is a leading chemicals company specialized in synthesizing and distributing organic chemicals and inorganic chemicals to various sizes and fields of industry. We were established in year 1982 based in Ipoh Perak, Malaysia. In response to business expansion and tremendous demand from the market, we have opened up a sales office in Penang in year 2005.\r\n\r\nWe act as a subsidiary of Samchem Holdings Berhad in year 2008 and work as a Branded distributor for ExxonMobil Chemical (EMC) products in Northern Region of Peninsular Malaysia.', 41, '17, Persiaran Rishah 14, Kawasan Perindustrian Silibin, 30100 Ipoh, Perak', '05 - 526697', 'enquiry@ewenychemicals.com.my', 'http://www.ewenychemicals.com.my', 'September-12-2012-3-35-pm-index_02.gif', 0, 5237),
(276, 'ABX EXPRESS (M) SDN BHD', 'ABX EXPRESS started it''s Malaysia and Brunei operations 26 years ago in Labuan and has since grown to service the whole nation through our own Network of 63 offices/service centers.\r\n\r\nWe are a Bumiputra-owned company.\r\n\r\nThe injection of senior management from the major players in the industry, combined with a team of more than 800 trained staff countrywide, has enabled us to deliver quality service which even our competitors talk about.\r\n\r\nOur logistics infrastructure enhances the partnership with our Customers through greater efficiency and productivity, ensuring cost-effective quality solutions.\r\n\r\nABX EXPRESS provides door-to-door express delivery of documents and packages.\r\n\r\nOur state-of-the-art computer tracking system, can reveal the precise status of your packages from pick-up point to final destination.\r\n\r\nABX''s express service is the most cost-effective convenient way to swiftly and safely dispatch your important business correspondence and package within Malaysia and the World. Our commitment is to give a little more than everyone else ...... \r\nDelivering Satisfaction Worldwide.', 56, 'ABX EXPRESS (M) SDN BHD Lot 8, Batu 10 Federal Highway, Sg Way 47300 Petaling Jaya  Selangor', '03-7711 668', ' customerservice@abxexpress.com.my', 'http://www.abxexpress.com.my', 'September-12-2012-3-49-pm-abx.jpg', 0, 5239),
(277, 'FM Global Logistics (M) Sdn. Bhd.', 'Incorporated in 1988, Freight Management is a wholly Malaysian owned international freight service provider. Its holding arm, Freight Management Holdings Bhd was listed on Bursa Malaysia Second Board (formerly KLSE) on 3 February 2005, and successfully transferred to the Main Board on 19th Dec 2007.\r\n\r\nIn 1999, Freight Management pioneered containerised rail freight services between Malaysia and Thailand , taking advantage of rising trade movement with the advent of AFTA (Asean Free Trade Area).\r\n\r\nToday, FMHB offers complete multimodal international freight services covering sea, rail, air freight and tuge barge services, customs brokerage and distribution container haulage and conventional trucking services.\r\n\r\nThe Freight Management Group has offices located in Port Klang, KLIA, Penang, Ipoh, Malacca and Johor to cover all the important maritime and air gateways of Malaysia.', 56, 'Lot 37, Lebuh Sultan Mohamad 1, Kawasan Perindustrian Bandar Sultan Suleiman, 42000 Port Klang', '03-3176 111', 'gen@my.fmgloballogistics.com', 'http://www.fmmalaysia.com.my', 'September-12-2012-4-36-pm-freightmgmt1a_01.jpg', 0, 5242),
(278, 'TNT Express Malaysia', 'TNT''s success, growth and leadership position in our industry depends largely on the energy and efforts of all our employees, serving our customers in all corners of the world. They are the people who make TNT a great company.\r\n\r\nIn all their various capacities, our people are the heart of our company.They always will be, because theres something fundamental that unites us in a common cause: every one of us is working in a service business.That means our people are the key determinant of our continuing success.\r\n\r\nTNT operates in 63 countries, all of which reflect a multitude of cultures, nationalities, religions, expertise and ideas. We have an extremely diverse customer base and, in order to achieve the highest levels of customer satisfaction, we need to reflect diversity within our organisation.\r\nWe focus on building an inclusive culture. We have networks in place to support employees with different backgrounds and beliefs and we work in partnership with local organisations to support people with fewer opportunities but greater skills.\r\n\r\nThe commitment and creativity of all our people has enabled TNT to consistently reach and exceed our profit and value targets, even in years when growth has been hard to find. Because we continue to grow, were continually on the look-out for excellent new people at every level whod like to share the passion and pride of the around 161,500 people in 63 countries around the world already serving TNTs customers.', 56, '-', '-', 'my.hrm@tnt.com ', 'http://www.tnt.com', 'September-12-2012-4-45-pm-logo_image_uploaded_on_15th_january_2009.jpg', 0, 5243),
