(295, 'Polydamic Holdings Sdn Bhd', 'Polydamic Holdings Sdn. Bhd. was incorporated in 10 March 1996 with Mr. Jacky Tan Eng Seng as the Managing Director. It was borne out of a passionate dream of Mr. Jacky Tan, the importance of a pristine environment free of pollutants. He set out to help the environment by the way he knows best, the manufacturer of innovative equipment and environmental consultation services which help to reduce pollutants when applied in different industries such as chemical, electronics, pharmaceutical, rubber glove, palm oil, electro-plating, water treatment and many others.\r\n\r\nPolydamic Holdings Sdn. Bhd. was incorporated in 10 March 1996 with Mr. Jacky Tan Eng Seng as the Managing Director. It was borne out of a passionate dream of Mr. Jacky Tan, the importance of a pristine environment free of pollutants. He set out to help the environment by the way he knows best, the manufacturer of innovative equipment and environmental consultation services which help to reduce pollutants when applied in different industries such as chemical, electronics, pharmaceutical, rubber glove, palm oil, electro-plating, water treatment and many others.\r\n\r\nIn the ever increasing industrialization of countries around the world and rampant pollution as a by-product of various industries, Polydamic contributes to reducing the environmental pollution through the promotion of the usage of our environmental control equipment and system in and outside Malaysia. Our company helps to heal the environment by manufacturing various high quality and reliable pollution-reducing products for use in industries which release pollutants into the air, land and water.\r\n\r\nThe company aim to remain as the leading environment control equipment manufacturer and also environmental engineering services and solutions provider which includes professional consultations, designing, development and manufacturing in and outside the region such as the air pollution control system; chemical and corrosion control system; chemical and process piping system; fiberglass engineering and fabrication; industrial engineering and machinery; fans; local exhaust ventilation as well as Department of Environment submission.\r\n\r\nPolydamic is a staffed by an elite team of highly dedicated and competent people that will meet all our customers needs and specifications. The company has provided environmental solutions for all kinds of industries over the years and has gained extensive experience, knowledge and expertise which are continuously updated.\r\n\r\nOur export markets include Indonesia, Philippines, Singapore, United States of America, China, Vietnam, Thailand, Sri Lanka, India, South America, France, Cambodia, Australia, Iraq, Jordan and Middle East.\r\nThe company has won several reputable awards including:\r\nThe 5th Malaysias 100 Outstanding SMEs  Golden Bull Award 2007\r\nThe 6th Asia Pacific International Honesty Enterprise - Keris Award 2007\r\nThe 3rd Asia Pacific Super Excellent Brand - Service Excellent Award 2007\r\nThe SME Recognition Award - Rising Star Award 2008\r\nThe Winner of Most Competitive SME Award 2010 By The Ministry of Human Resources Malaysia\r\nInnovation Certification for Enterprise Rating Transformation - The SME Innovation Award 2011\r\nSME Green Excellence Award - SME Recognition Award 2011\r\nThe BrandLaureate in Corporate Branding Air Pollution Control Systems - SME''s Best Brands Awards 2011\r\n ', 42, 'No.19, Lengkok Jelapang Maju,  Taman Perindustrian Ringan Jelapang Maju,  30020 Ipoh, Perak, Malaysia', '05-526 8198', 'polydamic@polydamic.com.my', 'http://www.polydamic.com.my', 'September-18-2012-3-45-pm-polydamic_logo.jpg', 0, 5301),
(296, 'Infrakomas Sdn Bhd ', 'Infrakomas Sdn Bhd was incorporated in year 1983. Originally, we specialised in the provision of designing, installing and commissioning of 33kV and 132kV for underground power cables inclusive of joints and terminations. Our services have now expanded in areas such as design, procurement, installation, testing, commissioning, and maintenance of Electrical, Mechanical and Civil installations. At Infrakomas, we regularly seek to hire outstanding individuals to join us on board our journey towards excellence', 76, '2, Jalan Pengetua U1/32 , Hicom-Glenmarie Industrial Park, 40150 Shah Alam, Selangor', '03-5569 323', 'infrakomas@ifk.com.my', 'http://www.ifk.com.my', 'September-18-2012-3-46-pm-infrakomas.jpg', 0, 5302),
(297, 'Lion Group ', 'The Lion Group is an established and progressive Group of Companies with diversified interests in Malaysia and the Peoples'' Republic of China.\r\n\r\nThe career development of its staff is and remains a priority of the Group''s. Continuous training programmes are arranged for all levels of staff to upgrade their skills within the Group''s ''continuous learning'' environment. The Group is also moving forward to having a flatter organisation which will lead to greater empowerment and provide even more opportunities for the staff to grow and contribute towards achieving the Group''s mission - to be a caring organisation, recognised for excellence in quality, growth and profitability.\r\n\r\nThe Lion Group today is moving ahead with a corporate culture that practises commitment, honesty & integrity and team spirit as core values; and a fundamental principle of being customer-oriented in every aspect, as reflected in its open and conducive work environment, quality products and services, and customer satisfaction.\r\n\r\nIn line with our succession plans, there are now opportunities for suitably qualified and highly motivated professionals to take up the following position to face the challenges in the new millennium. ', 30, 'Level 11 - 15, Office Tower No. 1 Jalan Nagasari (Off Jalan Raja Chulan) 50200 Kuala Lumpur', '03 - 2142 0', 'corpcomm@lion.com.my', 'http://www.liongroup.com.my', 'September-18-2012-4-14-pm-logo.jpg', 0, 5304),
(298, 'Chien Jin Plastic Sdn Bhd', '-', 42, '4 & 6 Persiaran Perusahaan , Kledang Utara 1/13 , Taman Perindustrian Chandan Raya , 31450 Mengelembu , Ipoh , Perak Darul Ridzuan.', '05-2822288', 'daniels@chienjin.com ', 'http://www.chienjin.com/', 'September-18-2012-4-32-pm-chien_jin_plastic.jpg', 0, 5303),
(299, 'Marrybrown Sdn Bhd', 'Established in 1981, they now have over 400 outlets serving Fried Chicken, Burgers, Seafood, Rice Base Products, Noodles, Porridge, Finger Foods, Desserts and Beverages. In 1980s Marrybrown became the first local fast food chain to franchise its business system in Malaysia. This was followed by many others who started to making it big in Malaysia franchise business.They serve Malaysian food such as Nasi Lemak and curry noodles', 24, 'No. 111A-B, Jalan Sri Pelangi, Taman Pelangi, 80400 Johor Bahru, Johor', '07 - 331659', 'qsr@marrybrown.com', 'www.marrybrown.com', 'September-18-2012-4-33-pm-marrybrown-franchise-opportunity1.jpg', 0, 5305),
(300, 'Striker Crushing & Screening Sdn Bhd', 'Striker commenced operations in Australia 1998 to service and supply the Quarrying, Mining, Civil Contracting, Earthmoving and Materials Handling industries with quality Crushing, Screening and Materials Handling equipment.\r\n\r\nFrom its first day, Striker has applied a flexible approach to each project and worked closely with our clients to ensure the desired client result is achieved, and this has proved instrumental in Striker winning valuable business throughout Australia and SE Asia.\r\n\r\nStriker has also expanded its range of equipment from wheel mounted, to track mounted and now the NEW range of modular plant to suit the Quarry and Mining industries. The range of equipment offered by Striker is one of the most comprehensive ranges available on the market, and covers applications from processing of C & D waste through to Fixed installation Iron Ore plants.\r\n\r\nStriker can also provide sales and hire, engineering functions, design, fabrication, supply and installation, repair and refurbish, project management, parts and accessories.\r\n\r\nPlease contact us for further details of the large range of Crushing, Screening and Asphalt solutions we provide.', 30, 'Plot No. 44, PT8286, Jalan Johan 2/4, Estate Perindustrian Pengkalan 2, Fasa 2,  31550 Pusing, Batu Gajah, Perak, Malaysia.', '05 366 8188', 'info@strikercrushing.com.my', 'http://www.strikercrushing.com.my', 'September-19-2012-9-21-am-striker.jpg', 0, 5313),
(301, 'GATEWAY INDUSTRIALCORPORATION SDN. BHD.', 'GIC- SPECIALIZES in the distribution of ISO certified & cost effective fire clay and high alumina refractory bricks and related matters which service the ceramic, chemical & energy industries.\r\n\r\nWE DELIVER customized design & material specifications to meet any unique requirements & complete technical support from conceptual to eventual installation.\r\n\r\nWE PROVIDE personalised service by an experienced work force and an effective distribution network located strategically in China and Malaysia.\r\n\r\n', 37, '74-76, Laluan Rasi Jaya 8,  Taman Rasi Jaya,  31450 Menglembu, Perak, Malaysia.', '05-282 8946', 'lucy@gicmy.com', 'http://www.gicmy.com', 'September-19-2012-9-41-am-logo.png', 0, 5314),
(302, 'KPMG IPOH', 'KPMG provides audit, tax & advisory services. We work closely with our clients, helping them to mitigate risks and grasp opportunities.\r\n\r\nOur reputation is created by the way the people within our member firms act with clients, colleagues and their communities.\r\n\r\nPutting our skills to work\r\nCitizenship is embedded in the KPMG values and we recognize our firms have the scale, influence and business knowledge to make a significant and positive contribution to the issues that affect our communities and environments. Find out more about our Corporate Citizenship strategy and how we are putting our skills to work.\r\n\r\nKPMG firms are worlds leading providers of audit, tax & advisory services. We operate in 152 countries & have 145,000 people around the world.\r\n\r\nCombined revenues for KPMG member firms totaled $22.7 billion for FY ending Sep 30, 2011, a 10.1% rise in U.S. dollars, or 6.2% in local currency', 1, '-', '05 2531 188', 'info@kpmg.com.my', 'http://www.kpmg.com', 'September-19-2012-10-06-am-kpmg.jpg', 0, 5315),
(303, 'IPOH INTERNATIONAL ANIMAL FEED (M) SDN. BHD', 'Ipoh International Feed was established in October 2008. A company \r\nspecially dealing in import and export animal feed.\r\n\r\n     In the earlier stage, every month in average we only sold 125 tons of\r\nfeed in the market. Nowadays in a month, in average we supply 10 \r\nthousands tons of feed in the market. Our success in not depending on \r\nluck, it is depending on our professional management and knowledge. By\r\nour hard work, within 3 years the business is growing and expanding \r\nsteadily.\r\n\r\n     As a feed supplier, we supply different varieties of feeds. These are \r\nsuitable for the fishery and husbandry.\r\n\r\n     We have the advantage because we can directly order the feed from\r\noverseas countries, not going through the agent. This is not only \r\nguaranteed the customers benefit, to reduce the cost effectively too.\r\n\r\n     In order to supply the varieties of feed, we have already established \r\nthe sale networks with other countries. These countries are India, \r\nBangladesh, Pakistan, Sri Lanka and the USA.\r\n\r\n     We consistently to keep our integrity and goodwill, to gain the \r\ncustomers confidence. To build up long term relationship with the\r\ncustomers. To keep the company growing continuously, to attain the\r\nwin-win business situation.', 4, 'No. 8A, Medan Istana 3, Bandar Ipoh Raya, 30000, Ipoh Perak, Malaysia.', '05 - 249 76', 'ipohfeed.msia@yahoo.com', 'http://ipohinternationalfeed.com.my', 'September-19-2012-10-32-am-ipohintfeed.jpg', 0, 5316),
(304, 'Maxis Berhad', 'To bring the future to our customers lives and business, in a manner that is simple, personalised and enriching, by efficiently and creatively harnessing leading-edge technology and delivering a brand of service experience that is reliable and enchanting. \r\n\r\n\r\nPart of our job at Maxis is to make sure that technology is never scary. Or even, remote from your daily activity. Our challenge is to answer successfully the question "how human can the technology become?" \r\n\r\nWe have four words to describe the spirit of Maxis, the things that should come across in every single thing that we do, for customers and for everyone who works together in the company. \r\n\r\nBy focusing on just four words we define ourselves. \r\n\r\nThis is what Maxis stands for.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe aim to keep everything we do as simple as possible. For example, customers understand what it is we are telling them because we do it in a way that is straightforward and easy to understand. \r\n\r\nWe make things simple for everyone, including ourselves. Keeping things simple also means that everything we say is said in a clear direct tone of voice that is friendly and human.\r\n\r\nTrust is crucial in every successful relationship and this is true between customers and Maxis, just as it is true between the company and its employees. All good relationships are built on trust which inspires confidence, and, assurance, conviction and reliance. \r\n\r\nTo be trustworthy is a way of life.\r\n\r\n\r\nCreativity defines us and therefore differentiates us from our competition. It inspires not only our communication style, but also how we answer the phone, design our stores, and deal with challenges. \r\n\r\nCreative runs through everything we do and everything we say, it''s in our DNA.\r\n\r\n\r\nTo lead people into new territories we have to be brave. We have the courage to try new things, to take the occasional calculated risk, to go where our competitors have not been. It ensures that we stay at the forefront and that our customers benefit from new and better ways of doing things. \r\n\r\nIt means doing the right thing, rather than the easy thing. It means having the courage of our convictions. Brave is the quality of a true leader.', 53, 'Maxis Berhad Corporate Affairs Level 22, Menara Maxis Kuala Lumpur City Centre 50088 Kuala Lumpur', '03 2330 700', 'adsales@maxis.com.my', 'http://www.maxis.com.my', 'September-19-2012-12-21-pm-maxisCom_MaxisLogo.gif', 0, 5317),
(305, 'MIMOS BERHAD', 'Gain a new perspective on MIMOS and understand our continuing role and relevance in positioning Malaysia as a regional centre of excellence.\r\n\r\nMIMOS is abound with a dynamic network of highly motivated and skilled people from various countries.  Our core values, internal and external training programmes, pre-service and in-service scholarships and cultural diversity are designed to assist employees in creating clearer career objectives and development plans.\r\n\r\nCombined with a flat and team-oriented organisation structure, we provide a stimulating and cooperative working environment for you to excel. With Innovation for Life as our tagline, we also reward our employees for submitting inventions, through various schemes, including cash rewards.  We look forward to sharing our successes together.  If you are keen to explore too, send us your resume at staffing@mimos.my.', 82, 'MIMOS BERHAD Technology Park Malaysia 57000 Kuala Lumpur Malaysia', '03 8995 500', ' staffing@mimos.my', 'http://www.mimos.my', 'September-19-2012-2-07-pm-mimos.png', 0, 5321);
