(306, 'The Store Headquarters Malaysia', 'The Store Corporation Berhad is a leading operator of supermarkets, departmental stores and hypermarkets in the country. Not only is The Store Corporation Berhad recognised as the largest supermarket and departmental chain by The Malaysia Book of Records (since 2001), it is also the oldest existing supermarket cum departmental chain in Malaysia. In 2008, The Store Corporation Berhad is celebrating its 43rd anniversary since its first outlet at Jalan Besar in Bukit Mertajam opened on 28 November 1968.\r\n\r\nThe Store Corporation Berhad has been listed on Bursa Malaysia since 3 March 1994. The Store Corporation Berhad is the only Malaysian retailer with outlets established in every state of the Peninsular Malaysia, with 51 supermarkets & departmental stores operating in the name of ''The Store'' under the legal entity The Store (Malaysia) Sdn. Bhd. The Store Group also operates hypermarkets through its wholly-owned subsidiary Pacific Hypermarket & Departmental Store Sdn. Bhd. At present, the Pacific group has 7 outlets at Star Parade and Alor Star Mall (both in Alor Star, Kedah), Megamal Pinang in Seberang Perai Tengah, Pulau Pinang, KB Mall in Kota Bharu, Kelantan, Batu Pahat Mall in Batu Pahat, Johore, and the new outlets at Pacific Komtar in Georgetown, Pulau Pinang and Kluang Mall in Kluang, Johore. Milimewa Superstore Sdn. Bhd., which operates 17 supermarkets and departmental stores in Sabah, has been under The Store Group since May 2005 and is The Store Corporation Berhad''s retail arm in East Malaysia and a strategic foothold for future expansion.\r\n\r\nPacific Hypermarket & Departmental Store Sdn. Bhd. was incorporated in Malaysia on 27 September 1995 under the Companies Act, 1965 as a private limited company. The company is principally involved in hypermarket and departmental store business with investment holdings.\r\n\r\nPacific Hypermarket & Departmental Store carries a wide assortment of merchandise, ranging from fresh market, groceries, sundries, and toiletries; to apparels, cosmetics, footwear, furniture, electrical and household items.\r\n\r\nThe business concept of Pacific Hypermarket and Departmental Store Sdn. Bhd. can be expressed as follow:-\r\n\r\nHypermarket business is conceptualized with the aim of offering more value for shopping in a no-frills environment. "Jimat Setiap Hari", this motto serves as a focal point in Pacific''s concept, where quality goods are offered at reasonable prices and is one of the main attraction factors for shopping at Pacific hypermarkets.\r\nDepartmental store outlets are a highly-targeted retail business with merchandise and goods that appeal more to fashion-conscious shoppers. It is a specialty-driven store that offers a wide variety of choices to fulfill the demand of today''s upwardly-mobile customers. The Store Corporation Berhad has been listed on Bursa Malaysia since 3 March 1994. The Store Group also operates hypermarkets through its wholly-owned subsidiary Pacific Hypermarket & Departmental Store Sdn. Bhd. At present, the Pacific group has 7 outlets at Star Parade and Alor Star Mall (both in Alor Star, Kedah), Megamal Pinang in Seberang Perai Tengah, Pulau Pinang, KB Mall in Kota Bharu, Kelantan, Batu Pahat Mall in Batu Pahat, Johore and the new outlets at Pacific Komtar in Georgetown, Pulau Pinang and Kluang Mall in Kluang, Johore.\r\n\r\nAt present, the company has seven outlets, which are located as detailed below:\r\n\r\na)	\r\nPacific (Star Parade), Alor Star, Kedah\r\n 	 \r\nb)	\r\nPacific (Alor Star Mall), Alor Star, Kedah\r\n 	 \r\nc)	Pacific (Megamal Pinang), Seberang Perai Tengah, Pulau Pinang\r\n 	 \r\nd)	Pacific (KB Mall), Kota Bharu, Kelantan\r\n 	 \r\ne)	Pacific (Batu Pahat Mall), Batu Pahat, Johore\r\n 	 \r\nf)	Pacific (Komtar), Georgetown, Pulau Pinang\r\n 	 \r\ng)	Pacific (Kluang Mall), Kluang, Johore\r\nPacific Hypermarket & Departmental Store Sdn. Bhd. is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Pacific Hypermarket Group Sdn. Bhd. with its ultimate holding company being The Store Corporation Berhad, a company listed on the Main Market of Bursa Malaysia Securities Berhad.', 47, 'SRI PETALING  41, Jalan Radin Tengah, Bandar Baru Sri Petaling,  57000 Kuala Lumpur. ', '016-3052873', 'recruitment@tstore.com.my', 'http://www.tstore.com.my', 'September-21-2012-10-02-am-the_store.jpg', 0, 5339),
(307, 'Tesco Stores (Malaysia) Sdn Bhd', 'We operate in Malaysia in partnership with local conglomerate, Sime Darby, who hold a 30% stake in the business. Since entering back in 2002 we have opened 45 stores across Peninsular Malaysia, with a combined floor space of almost 4m sq ft today. Our supply chain includes 2 state-of-the-art distribution centres, one for Fresh Food located in Perak and another Ambient Products located in Selangor.\r\nWe have a strong track record of supporting local SMEs and small traders and offer a special Clubcard for business customers  to specially meet the needs of local operators. We also support small retailers by offering technical advice, training and support, as well as preferential access to the Tesco supply chain and reduced rates at our malls, to help them develop and compete.', 47, 'Head Office, Level 3, No.3, Jalan 7A/62A, Bandar Menjalara, 52200 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.', '012-4088064', 'Zaharuddin.Zainol@my.tesco.com', 'http://www.tesco.com.my', 'September-21-2012-10-35-am-tesco.jpg', 0, 5341),
(308, 'Court Mammoth', 'Courts (Malaysia) Sdn Bhd (COURTS), the countrys largest consumer electronics and furniture retailer, recently opened their Ipoh Garden store with an array of major discounts and activities that would carry on for one month.\r\n\r\nThe initial celebration drew a large turn-out of Ipoh customers, who, for the past 23 years, have considered Courts as a top retail destination for its wide selection of LCD/LED TVs, customised and tailor-made sofas at affordable prices, and its wide range of branded beddings.\r\n\r\nCourts has found a new home in Ipoh since it first opened in Jalan Pasir Puteh back in 1998. Having moved its location to Persiaran Medan Ipoh between the years, the new Courts Ipoh Garden now joins the Perak store network along with other stores in Sitiawan, Kulim and Kamunting.\r\n\r\nThe strategic relocation of its Ipoh Garden branch brings improvements to the store layout and design, creating a greater shopping environment for customers. The new layout allows room for a variety of the latest products in digital and consumer electronics, such as the first store display of 3D TV in Ipoh.\r\n\r\nCustomers are invited to join in the four-week celebration where big door-busters discounts are given away such as cameras as low as RM99, mobile phones at RM88, coffee makers and blenders at RM20, shoe racks at RM1 and many more.\r\n\r\nThese discounts are in line with Courts Price Promise 2010s commitment in providing genuine value to customers through deeper price cuts, greater savings, and improved services. Purchases can be made through Courts flexible payment schemes which allow customers to pay in cash, credit, or by instalment plans.\r\n\r\nCustomers will also be treated to a variety of fun-filled family activities hosted each week which includes free health screenings, Lion Dance performances, DJ and Music machine, free hot dogs and coffee, as well as balloons, sweets and clown performances for the children.\r\n\r\nCustomers can also sign up for the Courts Home Club membership for free where members are entitled to credit rebates, discount prices of up to 30 percent, free delivery, extra year warranty, exclusive event invitations, and merchants offers at selected retail partners.', 47, 'Jalan Tuanku Abdul Rahman, Kuala Lumpur', '03-26975393', 'Nazman@courts.com.my', 'http://www.courts.com.my', 'September-21-2012-11-37-am-courts.jpg', 0, 5344),
(309, 'UO Superstore', 'UO Superstore Sdn Bhd (formerly known as Uda-Ocean Sdn Bhd) was incorporated in Malaysia under the Act on 21st October 1992 as a private company limited by shares under the name of Uda-Ocean Sdn Bhd.\r\n\r\nThe first outlet was opened on 16th March 1993 at Petaling Street Kuala Lumpur followed by the opening of the Ipoh store on 11th May 1996, Plaza Angsana Tampoi Johor Bahru on 16th October 1997, Chow Kit Kuala Lumpur on 25th June 2004, Pantai Hill Park Kuala Lumpur on 31st March 2006, Plaza Kotaraya Johor Bahru on 22nd September 2006, Galaxy Ampang Kuala Lumpur on 9th February 2007, Pasir Gudang Johor Bahru on 21st September 2007, Melawati Kuala Lumpur on 28th August 2009, Danga City Mall Johor Bahru on 15th November 2011, Batu Pahat Johor Bahru on 6th January 2012, Segamat Johor Bahru on 1st June 2012 and our latest outlet Kluang Johor Bahru on 27th July 2012\r\n \r\nOur responsibility to our valued customers is to continue offering quality merchandise at bargain prices which is in line with our tag line: Untung Orangramai.\r\n\r\n', 47, 'Greentown Shopping Mall, Jalan Hospital, 30820 Ipoh, Perak', '05-2422 320', 'Irene_ding@uo.com.my', 'http://www.uo.com.my', 'September-21-2012-11-55-am-uo.jpg', 0, 5345),
(310, 'AEON HQ', 'AEON CO. (M) BHD. (formerly known as Jaya Jusco Stores Bhd.) is a leading retailer in Malaysia with a total revenue of RM3.73 billion in the financial year ended 31st December 2009. The Company was incorporated on 15 September 1984. AEON CO. (M) BHD. was set up in response to the Malaysian Governments invitation to AEON Japan to help modernise the retailing industry in Malaysia. The JUSCO name today is well established among Malaysians as well as foreigners, especially due to its association with the international AEON group of companies.\r\n\r\nAEON has established itself as a leading chain of general merchandise stores. AEONs constant interior redecoration of stores, to project an image designed to satisfy the ever changing needs and desires of consumers, is clear evidence of this. The Companys performance has been further enhanced by the managements acute understanding of target market needs and the provision of a correct product-mix.\r\n\r\nAEONs stores are mostly situated in suburban residential areas, catering to the vast middle income group.\r\n\r\nThe AEON group of companies consists of AEON Co. Ltd., and more than 150 consolidated subsidiaries and affiliated companies. In addition to its core general merchandise stores (GMS) plus its supermarket and convenience store operations, AEON is also active in specialty store operations, shopping center development, operations and services.\r\n\r\nAEON group of companies is an integrated Japanese retailer and is active not only in Japan but also in Southeast Asia, China and North America.\r\n\r\nAt all times, in every market, AEON''s activities are guided by the unchanging ''Customer First'' philosophy. Its aim is to surpass expectations by combining excellent products with unique personal services that enhance the shopping experience to make the customers smile every time they shop.', 47, '3rd Floor, AEON Taman Maluri Shopping Centre, Jalan Jejaka, Taman Maluri, Cheras, 55100 Kuala lumpur.', '03-9207 200', 'watynoorlily@aeonretail.com.my', 'http://aeonretail.com.my', 'September-21-2012-12-22-pm-aeon.gif', 0, 5346),
(311, 'KAMDAR IPOH (Branch)', 'Kamdar Sdn Bhd was established in Malaysia since 1972, and has since achieved a dominant position in the garment and textile departmental store industry.\r\n\r\nThe Kamdar brand name has been well known for several generations. It has become part of Malaysian history, a fact of which Kamdar is very proud. Kamdar is well known for its extensive range and quality of garment and textile products. Kamdar stores specialize in textile fabric, furnishing fabric, in-house designed garments for ladies, men and childrens clothes, Indian clothing and school uniforms.\r\n\r\nThe Kamdar brand stands for quality of service, history and value for money. The company is perceived by the public as a trustworthy, value-for-money store with a difference. The Kamdar logo, with its distinctive typeface and green and white corporate colours  fostering an environmentally aware, clean, fresh and new image  is instantly recognisable throughout Malaysia.\r\n\r\nFINANCIAL FACTS\r\nIn 2004, Kamdar Group (M) Berhad was established as the holding company for the group in order to facilitate its listing on the main board of the KLSE.\r\n\r\nDespite the extremely intensive competition in the retail industry, Kamdar has grown turnover and earning impressively at the year 5-year CAGR of 8% and 10% respectively since 1996. compared to other listed retailers, Kamdar has the most superior PBT margin and second highest PBT-level among retailers in Malaysia.\r\n\r\nPERSONNEL\r\nAfter more than 50 years of growth, Kamdar has 28 outlets around Malaysia and employs about 1,200 staff.', 47, 'Ipoh No.32,Medan Stesen 19/7,Station 18, 31650 Ipoh Perak Darul Ridzuan', '05-3218866', ' ipohsec18@gmail.com', 'http://www.kamdar.com.my', 'September-21-2012-3-20-pm-kamdar.jpg', 0, 5349),
(312, 'KAMDAR SERI MANJUNG (Branch)', 'Kamdar Sdn Bhd was established in Malaysia since 1972, and has since achieved a dominant position in the garment and textile departmental store industry. The Kamdar brand name has been well known for several generations. It has become part of Malaysian history, a fact of which Kamdar is very proud. Kamdar is well known for its extensive range and quality of garment and textile products. Kamdar stores specialize in textile fabric, furnishing fabric, in-house designed garments for ladies, men and childrens clothes, Indian clothing and school uniforms. The Kamdar brand stands for quality of service, history and value for money. The company is perceived by the public as a trustworthy, value-for-money store with a difference. The Kamdar logo, with its distinctive typeface and green and white corporate colours  fostering an environmentally aware, clean, fresh and new image  is instantly recognisable throughout Malaysia. FINANCIAL FACTS In 2004, Kamdar Group (M) Berhad was established as the holding company for the group in order to facilitate its listing on the main board of the KLSE. Despite the extremely intensive competition in the retail industry, Kamdar has grown turnover and earning impressively at the year 5-year CAGR of 8% and 10% respectively since 1996. compared to other listed retailers, Kamdar has the most superior PBT margin and second highest PBT-level among retailers in Malaysia. PERSONNEL After more than 50 years of growth, Kamdar has 28 outlets around Malaysia and employs about 1,200 staff.', 47, 'Seri Manjung 1-7,Persiaran PM 2/1,Pusat Bandar Seri Manjung,Sec 2,32040 Seri Manjung,Perak.', '05-6888 866', 'serimanjung.kamdar@gmail.com ', 'http://www.kamdar.com.my', 'September-21-2012-3-25-pm-kamdar.jpg', 0, 5347),
(313, 'TF Value Mart (HQ)', 'TF Value-Mart has its beginnings as a Chinese medical shop in Bentong, Pahang. The Company first started operations as Chop Tong Fatt in 1957. Since then the Company has evolved through the years as a mini-market, departmental store and today as a thriving chain of hypermarket-concept outlets. We have adapted our retail format to meet changing consumer needs and will continue to do so to deliver the best value to our Customers. TF is abbreviated from "Thoong Fatt" which in Mandarin means to prosper together. And this has been the guiding principle in the Company''s conduct of its business. Our business philosophy is to ensure the best value for our Customers by working closely with our business partners to achieve this.\r\n\r\n', 47, 'No. 7 Sek 19  52 Jalan Ah Peng  28700 Bentong  Pahang Darul Makmur', ' 09-2221033', 'tfbentong@gmail.com ', 'http://www.tfvaluemart.com.my', 'September-21-2012-3-42-pm-TG_Logo.Gif', 0, 5350),
(314, 'MISC Berhad (Head Office)', 'At the heart of MISC''s culture is our belief in the strength of partnerships. Everyday is an opportunity to create new, formidable relationships as well as strengthening old ties - be it with our customers, shareholders, employees and even with the community.\r\n\r\nMISC''s environment encourages the growth of quality human capital, in all aspects, both professional and personal. We value work-life balance and promote physical and mental development in our people to support their professional development. And we also have fun along the way through sports, games as well as community services. \r\n\r\nWith over 42 years in the business, MISC is now the preferred provider of world-class maritime transportation and logistics services. What makes us stand apart from the rest is our team of professionals. Working with a wealth of resources and supported by both local and global partners, we continue to support the country''s aspiration to become a leading maritime nation.\r\n\r\nMISC continues to demonstrate superior dominance in the market in which we operate. We recognize that undoubtedly, it is the people behind MISC that make it happen. Our success however, was not built overnight. It is a culmination of ideas, strategies and strong corporate values - Loyalty, Integrity, Professionalism and Cohesiveness - that have stood the test of time and helped us become who we are today. \r\n\r\nWe are Malaysias largest shipping company and with businesses and strategic partnerships \r\naround the globe, we have made our mark as one of the top shipping companies globally.*         \r\nWe are the largest single owner-operator of LNG Carriers. We have a diversified, young and \r\nmodern fleet of ships with further new-builds on the way. Come on board with MISC and let \r\nyour maritime career soar with limitless possibilities', 41, 'Level 25, Menara Dayabumi Jalan Sultan Hishamuddin 50050 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia', '03 2264 088', 'seacareer@miscbhd.com', 'http://www.misc.com.my', 'September-21-2012-4-19-pm-MISC-Berhad.jpg', 0, 5352),
(315, 'Motosikal Dan Enjin Nasional Sdn Bhd (MODENAS)', 'Motosikal Dan Enjin Nasional Sdn. Bhd.\r\nMODENAS was established in tandem with Malaysia''s efforts to achieve industrialized nation status, now ubiquitously known as Vision 2020. MODENAS spearheads the technology transfer and development of motorcycle manufacturing, to eventually enable the country to proudly produce indigenous motorcycles. Although the vision will not be realised within a short time span, it is a strongly-held conviction that Malaysia will one day become one of the formidable manufacturers of motorcycles for worldwide distribution.\r\nKawasaki Heavy Industries (KHI) is the technology partner of MODENAS. Equity is shared by three parties - DRB-HICOM BERHAD (70%), KAWASAKI HEAVY INDUSTRIES (19%) and SOJITZ CORPORATION (Formerly Nissho Iwai Corporation, Japan) (11%).\r\nWith an investment of RM100 million, the MODENAS project was one of the fastest completed projects in the DRB-HICOM stable of companies. Building construction and infrastructure were completed in May 1996, within 9 months of the ground-breaking ceremony in August 1995. In June 1996, the first pilot unit rolled off the assembly facility.\r\n\r\nThe first 100 units of MODENAS motorcycles were then paraded in the 1996 Merdeka Day celebrations and the sales of MODENAS Kriss, the 4-stroke, 110 cc moped began in November 1996. Hardly one year after sales commenced in the domestic market, MODENAS launched its product in the international market on October 17, 1997.\r\n\r\nMODENAS'' achievements, from the first day the idea was mooted until the day the first model was introduced to the local market and then to the international market, were achieved through the sheer dedication and hard work of the management team and all the staff of MODENAS.\r\n\r\nMODENAS motorcycles are distributed by its wholly-owned subsidiary, EDARAN MODENAS SDN. BHD. (EMOS).\r\n\r\nMODENAS manpower generally comes from adjacent regions. Before assembly operations commenced , 200 MODENAS engineers and operators were sent to Japan for training.\r\n\r\nWhen operations began, the number of staff had swelled to 700 people, the majority being production operators. At the peak of production in 1997, almost 1000 people were employed in MODENAS.\r\n\r\nIf you are interested in employment with Modenas, please fill in the application form and submit it online or manually mail it to the appropriate address below. You will be contacted by phone if you meet the requirements for any positions currently open. Otherwise, your resume will be kept on file for at least one year.', 37, 'Human Capital Division Motosikal Dan Enjin Nasional Sdn Bhd (MODENAS) Kawasan Perindustrian Gurun, 08300 Gurun, Kedah Darul Aman', '04-466 8062', 'recruit@modenas.com.my', 'http://www.modenas.com.my', 'September-21-2012-4-35-pm-LogoMODENAS.jpg', 0, 5353),
(316, 'DRB HICOM', 'DRB-HICOM Berhad (DRB-HICOM) is one of Malaysias leading companies listed on the Main Market of Bursa Malaysia Securities Berhad, playing an integral role in the nations road to industrialisation. \r\n\r\nIn year 2000, DRB-HICOM formerly known as Diversified Resources Berhad undertook the merger of four listed companies within its stable namely, DRB-HICOM, Gadek, (Malaysia) Berhad, Gadek Capital Berhad and HICOM Holdings Berhad (HICOM) with an aggregate market capitalization in excess of RM6.0 billion. \r\n\r\nHICOM had been instrumental in leading the nations drive towards industrialisation and among its major achievements was the development of the National Car Project. Meanwhile, DRB-HICOM was instrumental in the development of Malaysias first national motorcycle and Malaysian-made truck in collaboration with international automakers. \r\n\r\nIn year 2006, the Group was acquired by Etika Strategi Sdn Bhd and became one of the three flagships of the AlBukhary Group of Companies. Accordingly, DRB-HICOM looks forward to harnessing synergies to be derived from the other AlBukhary flagships  engineering heavyweight, MMC Corporation Berhad and plantation, property and agro-based, Tradewinds Corporation Berhad and Tradewinds (M) Berhad. \r\n\r\nDRB-HICOM was in the vanguard of the nations foray into heavy industry and the Group has held fast to its original role of nation building. The Groups principal activities currently are in the automotive, services and property & infrastructure sectors. \r\n\r\nThe Groups automotive sector is involved in the manufacturing of components and the assembly and distribution of cars, trucks and motorcycles for the passenger, commercial, mass transport and defence automotive markets. In addition, the Group is also involved as an importer and service provider for CBU and CKD vehicles as well as pre-delivery inspection. \r\n\r\nThe services sector provides inspection of vehicles, solid waste management, insurance, full service provider for airlines and distributor for MIDEA, a leading brand in the white goods market. The services sector has been strengthened with the recent acquisition of Bank Muamalat Malaysia Berhad and Rangkai Positif Sdn Bhd which provides operations and maintenance services for Tanjung Bin Power Plant. \r\n\r\nThe property business is in development, engineering, infrastructure and construction. \r\n', 37, 'Level 6, Wisma DRB-HICOM  No.2, Jalan Usahawan U1/8, Section U1 40150, Shah Alam, Selangor', '03 2052 800', 'career@drb-hicom.com', 'http://www.drb-hicom.com', 'September-21-2012-4-45-pm-hicom_logo.gif', 0, 5354),
(317, 'Megasteel Sdn Bhd', 'Megasteel Sdn Bhd, a member of The Lion Group, is the first integrated steel mill in Malaysia to produce flat steel products with a capacity of 3.2 million tonnes of hot rolled coils and 1.45 million tonnes of cold rolled coils per annum. It has a total investment of RM3.2 billion and is located on a 500-acre site in Banting, Selangor. The mill is approximately 1.3 km long with a built-up area of 1.3 million square feet. It also produces hot rolled coils, pickled and oiled. \r\n\r\nMegasteel is in close proximity to the Klang valley where 70% of the nation''s consumers of hot rolled coils are located. Its strategic location near Port Klang helps to facilitate exports and lower transportation costs for the import of raw materials and export of finished coils. With a capacity of 2 million metric tons per annum, Megasteel''s production helps to substitute imports and yield substantial foreign exchange savings.\r\n\r\nThe Megasteel mill is fully automated using state-of-the-art direct current Electric Arc Furnace-Compact Strip Production (EAF-CSP) process which incorporates the ''Thin Slab Casting'' technology developed by SMS of Germany. \r\n\r\nCSP - Thin Slab Casting technology is recognised worldwide as the latest technology to produce flat steel. It is able to produce high quality steel with significantly higher production yield and energy savings. More importantly, Megasteel is more environment-friendly as it recycles steel scrap and uses the clean raw material, Hot Briquetted Iron (HBI) in its EAF process. Megasteel is the only steel mill in the country to use this advanced CSP technology. \r\n\r\nMegasteel also produces hot rolled coils, picked and oiled. It has commenced production of its cold rolled mill with a capacity of 0.7million metric tons expandable to 1.45 million metric tons of cold rolled coils per annum.', 37, 'MEGASTEEL SDN BHD Wisma Lion, Lot 2319, Kawasan Perindustrian Olak Lempit, Mukim Tanjung 12, 42700 Banting, Selangor Darul Ehsan', '016-303 090', ' hrp@megasteel.com.my', 'http://www.lion.com.my', 'September-21-2012-4-52-pm--megasteel.GIF', 0, 5356),
